title: mint tea
directions: Boil 2 quarts water.
Pour over tea bags and steep.
Remove tea bags and stir in sugar.
Stir in lemonade and limeade.	Add cold water to make 1 gallon.
Add mint when steeping.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Combine and cook until melted.
Add chicken.
Place a layer of crushed Doritos in a flat casserole dish, then add the chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Crushed chips can be sprinkled on top before baking, if desired.

title: indian bread
directions: Heat oil; drop by spoonfuls and deep fry.

title: egg and sausage souffle(servings:  4)
directions: Crumble and brown 1 pound mild sausage.
Drain and cool.
In a large bowl, beat 6 eggs.
Add milk, salt and dry mustard.
Add bread cubes.
Stir.
Add cheese and browned sausage; mix well. This must be refrigerated overnight.
Next morning, place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sis's pumpkin pie
directions: Bake at 375° or 400° until done.
Fills 2 deep crusts.

title: citrus steak
directions: Brown cubed steak.
Layer with lemon, orange and onion. Add salt
and
pepper
to
taste and tomato sauce.
Cover and simmer 35 to 45 minutes on medium heat.

title: vanilla wafer tarts
directions: Put cupcake liners in muffin pans.
Put wafer in bottom of liner.
Cream the cream cheese and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs. Mix well.
Pour batter into cupcake liner.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
When cool, spoon on pie filling as topping.

title: turkey barley soup
directions: Combine stock, onion and barley in soup kettle.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add potatoes and carrots and simmer 20 minutes more. Stir in turkey, peas and pepper.
Simmer 5 minutes more.
Serves 8.

title: lemon seven-up cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl; beat well.
Pour into ungreased angel cake pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: clams casino
directions: Simmer clams and lemon juice for 15 minutes.
In a small skillet, saute onion, garlic, margarine, parsley flakes, oregano, black pepper and Tabasco.
Mix all in a 1-quart casserole; add bread crumbs.
Top with cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve warm with crackers.

title: swedish rusks
directions: Brown almonds in oven.
Mix eggs, sugar and oleo together. Add milk, soda and flavoring.
Gradually add flour.
Stir in nuts. Form into 2 long rolls on cookie sheet.
Can add more flour if too sticky to handle.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Cut on angle in slices.
Lay out on cookie sheet and dry at 200° for 45 minutes, turning once.

title: cranberry crest
directions: Grind cranberries.
Add sugar and drained pineapple.
Set aside.
In another bowl, stir together marshmallows and whipping cream.
Cover both bowls and refrigerate 2 1/2 hours then stir ingredients in both bowls together.

title: baked vidalia onion dip
directions: Combine cheese, onion and mayonnaise and stir well.
Spoon mixture into a greased 1-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 325°
for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve with crackers, bread cubes or corn chips.

title: cabbage casserole #2
directions: Put shredded cabbage
in baking dish.
Pour potato soup and water over cabbage.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven until cabbage
is
tender.
Sprinkle
on bread crumbs and bake until crumbs are lightly brown.

title: cinnamon sticks
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolk and vanilla.
Add flour and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Brush beaten egg white over surface.
Press in 1 cup finely chopped nuts (pecans) into dough.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven; cut into strips while hot and remove from pan to cool.
Delicious!

title: marshmallow salad
directions: Cream cheese and salad dressing.
Add pineapple and juice, marshmallows and prepared Dream Whip.
Add nuts, if desired.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Wash tomatoes.
Cut into thin slices.
Sprinkle with salt; let stand, covered, overnight.
Rinse with water.
Slice onions, chop peppers.
Add sugar and vinegar, dissolve over heat.
Place all spices loosely in a double cheesecloth bag.
Add tomatoes and spice bag.
Simmer 1 hour.
Pour into scalded jars, seal.
Makes about 7 pints.

title: lemon chicken supreme
directions: Add melted oleo, lemon juice and paprika.
Dust garlic salt on chicken and dip each in butter mixture.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Spread on soup and mushrooms.
Sprinkle almonds on top. Bake another 20 to 30 minutes watching close so almonds don't burn.
Mix sour cream to butter mixture heating on low to melt cream.
If sauce is not thick enough, add 1 tablespoon flour.
Add more lemon, if desired.
Spoon sauce over chicken and white rice when served.

title: green salad
directions: Mix pudding powder with undrained pineapple thoroughly. Mix with Cool Whip.
Turn
into
clear glass bowl and decorate top with drained cherries.
Walnuts and pecans can be mixed in or added on top if you want more nuts.

title: italian dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in covered jar in refrigerator until ready to use.
Shake well before using.
Makes 3/4 cup.

title: german apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs until foamy, then add the oil and mix well.
Add sugar, vanilla, spices, soda and flour, mixing after each addition.
Stir in nuts and apples.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cool and frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mash baked potatoes.
(Boiling potatoes instead of baking removes much of the flavor).
Add to potatoes, the eggs, sugar and spice.
(I prefer allspice, nutmeg and grated dried orange rind.) Pour into 2 pie shells and dot with butter chips.
Start oven temperature at 400°.
Fifteen minutes later, reduce to 375°. Fifteen minutes later, reduce to 350°.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes longer.
Toward end of baking time, marshmallows may be added to top and baked until toasted.

title: fudge cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or 2 round 8 or 9 1/2-inch layers.

title: black forest torte
directions: Brush sides and bottoms of 4 (9-inch) cake pans with chiffon soft-type margarine.
Sift into large mixing bowl flour, sugar, soda, salt and baking powder.
Add chiffon, melted chocolate, water and vanilla.
Beat at low speed to blend, then beat for 2 minutes at medium speed, scraping sides and bottom of bowl frequently.
Add eggs and beat 2 minutes or until smooth.

title: carrot cake
directions: Flour and grease cake pan.
Mix all ingredients together and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries, soda and water for 10 minutes.
Take from heat and add marshmallows, jello and sugar.
Let set until cold. Now add apples, celery and nuts.
Chill.

title: german potato salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, oil and vinegar until creamy.
Stir together potatoes, onion and mixture.
Experiment with vinegar.
Some like more than others.

title: 5 minute fat-free chili
directions: In medium saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes over medium heat.
Garnish with cheese and onion.
Serves 4.
Calories: 160.
Fat: 0.

title: velvety white cake(two 8-inch layers)
directions: Mix dry ingredients well; add fat and half of milk.
Beat until creamy.
Add remaining milk, egg whites and flavoring.
Beat until creamy.
Pour into two 8-inch greased and floured layered cake pans.
Bake at 375° (moderate oven) for 25 to 30 minutes, or until the cake surface springs back up when touched lightly.
Cool cake for a few minutes before removing from the pans.
When cool, frost as desired.

title: italian dressing
directions: Combine ingredients; shake or mix well until blended.
Put into pint bottle and refrigerate.
Shake well before using.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except noodles.
Mix well.
Pour over dry noodles and stir lightly. Bake at 375° for 1 hour, covered with foil.
When done, remove foil and sprinkle cheese over top.

title: dieter's key lime pie
directions: Dissolve jello in 1/4 cup hot water (not easy). Add yogurt and Cool Whip. Pour into crust. Chill in refrigerator.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix ingredients well in a large jar.
When needed, put 2 rounded teaspoonfuls into a 6-ounce teacup and fill with very hot water.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Heat on stove (medium heat), stirring constantly, until butter is melted. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° until done or about 30 minutes. Makes 2 pies.

title: brownies
directions: Cream sugar and butter or margarine.
Add beaten eggs and Hershey's chocolate syrup.
Add flour with baking powder.
Bake in jelly roll pan for 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: low-fat jello cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Bake at 350°
in 13 x 9 x 2-inch rectangular pan for 30 to 40 minutes. Cool. Prick the cake at 1/2-inch intervals with fork.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water and pour carefully over cake.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: crabmeat in garlic-cream sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pick through crabmeat in order to remove bits of shell.
Combine first 4 ingredients and set aside. Combine sour cream, wine, salt and pepper (black and cayenne). Fold cream mixture into crabmeat mixture carefully so as not to break up the crabmeat.
Place mixture into 4 (1-cup) au gratin dishes or in 1 (1-quart) casserole dish.
In a small bowl, combine bread crumbs and cheese with a fork.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake until golden and bubbly, 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: kristen's favorite breadsticks
directions: Let yeast and water work.
Mix together with salt, honey and flour (will be sticky).
Melt margarine on a cookie sheet.
Set oven at 350°.
Roll the dough in margarine.
Pull and twist it through the margarine.
Make two 4-inch rolls.
Cut into breadsticks; sprinkle with garlic salt and Parmesan cheese.
Let rise.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: creamy lemon bars
directions: Mix crumbs, sugar and margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press into bottom of pan.
Combine powdered sugar, cream cheese and 1 cup of Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.

title: sand cookies
directions: Combine ingredients in order given.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: dump salad
directions: In large bowl, mix ingredients together.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon soda. Stir.
Pour over popcorn.
Mix well.
Bake for 1 hour at 200°, stirring frequently.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Boil water, cornstarch and sugar.
Add strawberry jello.
Cool and add strawberries.
Pour into prebaked pie crust.

title: baked corn with chive sauce
directions: In a 1-quart casserole, combine whole kernel corn, cream cheese with chives, salt and pepper.
Cover and bake at 325° about 45 minutes.
Serve baked corn in sauce dishes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: super sunday lasagna
directions: In bowl, combine Ricotta, spinach, 1/2 of Mozzarella, Parmesan and eggs; mix well.
In 15 x 9-inch dish, layer sauce, lasagna and mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake an additional 10 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: stew's cheddar scones
directions: In a large bowl mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and garlic powder.
Add butter and cut in until crumbly, using two knives or your hands.
Add grated cheese and stir until well mixed.

title: edd's chocolate frosting
directions: Boil one minute.
Remove from heat.
Cool and beat mixture. Spread on cake.

title: cee's sour cream enchiladas
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients together.
In separate bowl, mix chilies, salsa and chicken.
In large, ovenproof dish, spread half of the soup mixture evenly over bottom.
Tear 6 tortillas and put over soup mixture.
Spread half of meat mixture and repeat layers. Cover with Cheddar-Jack cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bavarian apple torte
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Toss apples into the sugar mixture.
Spoon over cream cheese layer, sprinkle with almonds. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 400° and continue baking for 25 minutes.
Cool before removing rim of pan.

title: fruit soup(vin suppe)
directions: Soak tapioca in water 3 hours.
Drain; discard water.
Soak prunes and raisins in water 1 hour.
Drain; discard water.
Cook fruit in water to cover 15 minutes.
Add drained tapioca, lemon, cinnamon stick and 2 cups grape juice.
Cook until tender, adding more water or grape juice as necessary.
Add salt and sugar to taste.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill.
Serve with raw vegetables (especially good with raw cauliflower).

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple and juice in a saucepan.
Remove from heat. Add gelatin, stirring to dissolve.
Cool.
Fold in buttermilk, whipped topping and pecans.
Pour into square or oblong dish. Chill until firm.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil chicken and chop into small pieces when cool.
Make white sauce with butter, flour, salt and milk.
Add onion, pimento, chopped chicken, mushroom soup and half of cheese to white sauce.

title: quick applesauce nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in ungreased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Stir vigorously and scrape down sides.
Spread batter evenly in pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Loosen cake from sides and serve warm with Cool Whip.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix and press into sides of heavily greased spring-form pan. Chill.

title: dumplings made simple
directions: Place chicken breasts in Dutch oven; cover with water. Add salt, more or less as desired. Cook in boiling water for about 2 hours; cool and remove meat from bones. Mix flour and cream of chicken soup together. Drop by tablespoons onto hot chicken pieces in broth. Cook slowly for 10 minutes, uncovered, then cook 10 minutes tightly covered. Remove dumplings and meat from broth; make gravy, if desired. Serve!

title: scripture cake
directions: Season to taste with (2 Chronicles 9:9) spices.
Mix like a fruit cake and bake.

title: chop suey
directions: Fry hamburger.
Add onion, celery and tomato sauce.
Cook macaroni and add to mixture.
Drain corn and add.
Cook in casserole dish.
Add cheese to top and bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: orange cool and easy pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Stir until slightly thickened.
Stir in whipped topping until smooth; fold in orange sections.
Refrigerate 20 to 30 minutes until mixture will mound.
Spoon into crust and refrigerate 4 hours or until firm. Garnish with additional topping and orange slices.

title: fruit glow punch
directions: In large punch bowl, combine concentrates and apple juice. Stir in ginger ale.
Spoon sherbet into bowl.
Serve immediately. Makes 28 servings (about 1/2 cup each).

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix flour and corn.
Add sugar, milk, salt, pepper and butter. Stir in eggs.
Grease 1 quart casserole.
Pour in mixture.
Place casserole in pan of hot water.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve the yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar in 1 cup warm water. Add the shortening, sugar, salt, beaten eggs and 1 cup warm water. Add 3 cups of flour at first; beat with wire whisk, then add remaining flour, 1 cup at a time, stirring in with wooden spoon. Cover bowl; let rise 1 hour.
Flour board and roll out 1/2 of dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Spread with butter, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/2 cup brown sugar.
You can add more sugar so it makes its own glaze.
Roll up and cut into 1-inch slices to place in greased pan.
Let rise 2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: creme brulee
directions: Heat cream on top of double boiler.
Beat egg yolks in a bowl, then gradually mix in sugar. When cream is warm, gradually add to egg and sugar mixture, stirring constantly. Add vanilla and pour into brulee dishes.
Put individual dishes in a pan containing about 1/2-inch hot water.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle 1/2 teaspoon sugar on top of each dish.
Heat oven broiler and place dishes under broiler until the sugar on top just caramelizes. Cool and serve.

title: garlic sauce
directions: Cook garlic in butter and oil over medium-low heat just until soft, but not browned.
Stir in parsley and cook 1 to 2 minutes (stir continuous).
Spoon over cooked spaghetti.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs with sugar and margarine.
Pat into pan for crust on bottom of 9 x 12 pan.
Beat cream cheese. Add powdered sugar.
Prepare Dream Whip as directed on the package and add to cream cheese.
Mix and spread over the crust.
Top with the pie filling and refrigerate 12 to 24 hours before serving.

title: chicken orobianco
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before serving, in 12-inch skillet over medium heat in oil, cook garlic until golden; remove and discard garlic. In drippings, over medium heat, brown chicken and sausages, a few at a time. Pour off all but 2 tablespoons drippings. Return chicken and sausages to skillet. Stir in wine, mushrooms and salt; bring to boiling. Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender. Arrange chicken and sausages on warm platter. In cup, blend water and cornstarch until smooth. Stir into hot liquid; cook over medium heat until mixture thickens. Pour this wine and mushroom gravy over chicken and sausage pieces. Serve over noodles.

title: mexican flank steak
directions: Pound meat on both sides; sprinkle with garlic salt, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Unwrap tamales; place in bowl.
Break up slightly with fork; spread over steaks.
Roll up as for a jelly roll; tie closed.
Place in shallow baking pan. Dissolve bouillon in boiling water; mix with tomato sauce and hot pepper sauce.
Pour over meat.
Roast in 350° oven for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours, basting often.
Remove strings.
Top meat with cheese. Makes 6 servings.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese, together.
In a 9 x 13-inch greased pan (dish), pour 1/2 mix and 1/2 grated cheese. Add remaining mix and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Grate the cabbage.
Add the apple (chopped with skin on). Squeeze the lemon juice on the cabbage and apple.
Add the raisins and peanuts. Add sugar to taste and mix with mayonnaise.

title: zucchini pepper pie
directions: Saute zucchini, onions, bell pepper, tomato and spices until liquid has evaporated; about 30 minutes.
Pour sauteed ingredients into pie shell.
Mix eggs and cream and pour over vegetables. Cover with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven. Serves 6.

title: chili
directions: Melt shortening.
Saute onion and garlic.
Add meat.
Let turn grey.
Stir in flour, then add to the remaining ingredients in a small heavy pot.
Cook on low heat for 3 to 4 hours.

title: christmas beets
directions: Drain and chop beets.
Heat in microwave or on top of stove until warm.
Stir in French dressing.
Place in bowl.
Top with sour cream.
Sprinkle chopped green onions (include green tops) on top for garnish.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook and drain hamburger. Add cream of mushroom soup to hamburger and put in bottom of 13 x 9 dish. Add cheese then top with mashed potatoes. Cook at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: surprise meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well and shape into 8 equal servings or balls.
Flatten balls and roll a slice of bacon around outer edge of patty.
Secure or hold with toothpick.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Peel and halve eggs. Remove yolks and mash. Add all other ingredients to mashed yolks except paprika; mix well. Refill egg whites with yolk mixture. Sprinkle with paprika. Refrigerate until ready to use. Makes 8 servings.

title: egg casserole
directions: Boil and devil eggs and place in bottom of shallow casserole. Mix chipped beef, onion and sauce together.
Pour over eggs. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
This may be made ahead and refrigerated until cooking.
May be served over toast.

title: scalloped fish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place fish in an ungreased baking dish and dot with margarine.
In a saucepan over medium heat, slowly stir flour into milk.
Stir until thick and then cook 1 minute longer.
Stir in remaining ingredients and pour sauce over fish. Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
Bake, uncovered, 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baker's holiday marble bark
directions: *Or can use 6 squares bittersweet baking chocolate.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Scald 1 1/2 cups milk in top of double boiler.
Combine sugar, flour, cornstarch and salt.
Stir this flour mixture into hot milk.
Cook until thickened.
Remove from heat; add butter, vanilla and 3/4 cup coconut.
Allow mixture to cool, then pour into baked 9-inch pie shell.
Cover with meringue and remaining coconut.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until meringue browns lightly.

title: walnut roast
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small casserole dish sprayed with Pam and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with mushroom sauce (mushroom soup, sour cream and water).

title: butter rolls
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Put dough on dough board and knead until stiff enough to roll out.
Put butter and sugar on dough and roll up slices of 1/2-inch.
Put in baking dish and bake until done at 350°.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Soften cream cheese and margarine. Combine with flour to form soft dough. Place in Ziploc bag and refrigerate until cold. Remove from refrigerator and form 24 small balls. Put 1 formed ball in each of the 24 cups of a mini muffin pan. Press ball to mold against sides and bottom of pan. Set aside.

title: french ritz green beans
directions: Drain beans and mix with onions, pepper, sour cream, and soup. Add salt and pepper to taste. Pour into a 3 quart casserole dish sprayed with Pam. Melt margarine and mix with crushed crackers. Place crackers on top of casserole and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: easy coconut macaroons
directions: Blend together.
Drop by teaspoons 1 inch apart onto well-greased pan.
Bake at 350° until delicate brown (8 to 10 minutes).
Remove from pan at once.

title: zucchini bread with pineapple
directions: Mix well.
Bake in well-greased and floured loaf pans.
Makes 2 loaves.
Freezes well and keeps well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: fantastic frozen blueberry muffins
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla and mix thoroughly.
Mix in baking powder, salt, flour and milk.
Add blueberries and blend in by hand.
Spoon into paper lined muffin cups until 2/3 full.
Sprinkle with mixture of 2 tablespoons of sugar and 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, cocoa and butter in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, peanut butter, oats and nuts; mix well.
Drop by teaspoons on wax paper. Cookies will be ready in a few minutes.
Yields 5 1/2 dozen.

title: cream of tomato soup
directions: In small stew pan, place tomato juice and place on stove to warm.
In larger pan, melt margarine; remove from heat.
Mix in flour, salt and pepper; stir until smooth.
Add milk and place on stove; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook until thickened; remove from heat.
Stir baking soda into warm tomato juice and then stir into gravy mixture.
Serve with crackers or garlic toast.

title: mama's homemade rolls
directions: To scalded milk, add sugar and Crisco. Let cool until lukewarm and dissolve yeast cake in it. Beat in the flour. Let rise for 30 minutes. Sift together and add to the mixture baking powder, sifted flour, soda and salt. Put in the refrigerator and let stay until next day. Take out of refrigerator; roll and fold then place in baking pan and let rise for 2 hours before baking at 400°.

title: spinach pie
directions: Boil spinach about 15 minutes.
Drain and press out water.
It has to be very dry.
Put butter in a saucepan and saute spinach 7 to 8 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Mix in the eggs, cheese, onion and dill.
Butter 265 mm x 375 mm (10 1/2 to 14 3/4-inch) baking dish.
Cover bottom with one pastry sheet.
If necessary use a piece of the other one.
Put all ingredients on pastry sheet. Cover with other sheet.
Butter surface and cut pie into pieces. Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a mixing bowl, combine first six ingredients.
Combine remaining ingredients; add to dry ingredients and stir only until moistened.
Pour into a greased 9-inch square baking pan or a 10-inch heavy skillet.
Bake 30 - 35 minutes, or until bread is golden brown and tests done.

title: franks and veggie hot pot
directions: Cut franks into 1-inch pieces.
Heat to boiling chicken broth and water.
Add macaroni, basil, salt and pepper.
Return to boiling.
Cook, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Stir in franks, vegetables and onion.
Simmer 5 minutes longer until macaroni is tender, vegetables are cooked and most of water is absorbed.
Fold in sour cream and mayonnaise.
Garnish with chopped parsley, chives or green peppers sprinkled on top if desired.
Makes four servings.

title: chicken ratatouille
directions: Chop onion, pepper and tomato.
Slice zucchini; mince garlic. Cut chicken crosswise into strips.
Saute onion and green pepper in 1 tablespoon oil until soft; add garlic and zucchini and cook 3 or 4 minutes.
Add tomato and cook 3 minutes.
Push aside; add remaining oil and add chicken until it begins to brown.
Stir in herbs, salt and pepper and cook until chicken is done and liquid evaporates.
Add lemon to serve.

title: sherried fruit casserole
directions: Drain all fruit.
Arrange fruit in layers in large casserole. In top of double boiler, combine sugar, flour, butter and sherry. Cook over hot water, stirring until smooth and thick.
Pour over fruit in casserole.
Cover casserole and refrigerate overnight.

title: potato puff casserole
directions: In skillet, cook
ground
beef, onion and peppers until meat is browned.
Add
vegetables
and cook until tender.
Add chili sauce, soup and
water.
Turn
into
quart casserole. Cover top with frozen
potato puffs.	Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 35 minutes or until potatoes are golden brown.

title: mushroom barley soup
directions: In a Dutch oven, melt butter; saute onion, green pepper (optional) and mushrooms.
Add and mix in flour.
Slowly add the consomme and milk, stirring to keep smooth.
Add the seasonings and the barley.
Bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes until barley is tender.
If it gets too thick, thin with milk or consomme.

title: corn pudding
directions: Drain corn and pour into a 2-quart microwave greased dish. Add flour and sugar.
In empty can, beat eggs and pour milk to fill can.
Mix with corn, flour and sugar.
Cover and microwave on 70% for 9 minutes.
Stir and cook, uncovered, on 70% for 6 to 7 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes.

title: swiss scrambled eggs
directions: Soak bread cubes in milk.
Drain after 5 minutes, saving milk. Combine eggs, salt, pepper and milk strained from bread cubes. Melt 2 tablespoons butter in pan and scramble eggs only until soft. Add soaked bread cubes.
Place in buttered 9-inch square dish. Arrange cheese slices over top.
Melt remaining butter with dry bread crumbs and sprinkle over cheese.
Top with bacon.
Place in hot oven at 400° until cheese bubbles (about 15 minutes if dish is cold; can make day ahead).
Serves 6.

title: waffles
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add milk, butter and oil, then add beaten egg yolks, then fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in hot waffle iron.
(Best made the day before cooking.)

title: peach cobbler
directions: Bring peaches, sugar and butter to a boil, then add nutmeg to taste.
To thicken, mix a little sugar and flour together and put into the peaches that are boiling.
Bake at 350°.
Put ingredients in pie shell.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together and shape into balls. Cook until golden brown.

title: rhubarb-strawberry clafouti
directions: Stir together eggs and flour in large bowl.
Stir in milk, cream, 5 tablespoons sugar and vanilla.
Use 1 tablespoon butter to generously grease 1 1/2-quart glass casserole.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix together and roll into balls.
Melt a block of semi-sweet chocolate and paraffin and dip each ball of candy.
Place on wax paper to dry.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil chicken until tender with salt and pepper.
Remove chicken from broth and allow to cool.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth. Remove skin from chicken and cut chicken in small pieces. Cook vegetables slowly in small amount of oil until tender. Combine chicken, vegetables and soup.
Mix and then combine drained spaghetti with other ingredients.
Add cheese and small amount of broth.
Place in casserole dish and dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together, chill and serve.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Fry sausage.
Place rice, sausage, milk, pepper, onion, soup, mushrooms and cheese in 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake uncovered 45 minutes at 350°.

title: italian love cake
directions: Mix cake as directed.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix Ricotta cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla together; spoon mixture on top of unbaked cake.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool and frost.
Refrigerate.

title: mediterranean feta pasta salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix juices per instructions.
Dissolve sugar in 5 cups of water.
Add remaining ingredients to sugar-water.
Freeze in Ziploc bags.
When ready to serve, thaw a little.
Add the ginger ale.
Stir until slushy.

title: aunt bill's microwave candy
directions: Combine sugar, soda, buttermilk and butter in a large microwavable bowl (mixture bubbles up while cooking).
Cover with plastic wrap; punch holes in wrap.
Microwave on High for 2 1/2 minutes, stir and turn dish.
Continue cooking for 15 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.
Return to microwave for 2 minutes or until soft ball forms in cold water or it tests 236° on a candy thermometer.
(Do not put candy thermometer in the microwave while cooking.)
Add vanilla and beat with electric mixer until soft peaks form.
Watch closely.
Stir in pecans and spread in buttered 12 x 7-inch dish.
Cool; cut into pieces.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Beat together the first 3 ingredients.
Mix the flour, salt, baking soda and fruit cocktail.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle coconut on batter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: pasta fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except apricots in large bowl; mixing well.
Spoon onto lettuce lined plate.
Arrange apricots around salad; top with additional cinnamon and sour cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spanish rice casserole for 100!
directions: Brown meat.
When meat is half done,
add
onion,
onion powder, salt and green pepper.
When the meat
is
light brown, add
the remaining ingredients and cook for
minutes.
Stir continuously.
Wash rice, cook for 15 minutes.
Rinse
and	add to cooked ingredients.
Put in 18 x 24 x
2-inch
pan	and
add shredded cheese on top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: rustlers apple crumble
directions: Place apples in a 2-inch high buttered dish.
Sprinkle with salt, cinnamon and 1/4 cup water.
Mix together sugar, flour and butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples and bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Mash chilies and add to soups and milk.
Heat to blend.
Put one layer of tortillas and one layer of chicken.
Cover with sauce, then cheese.
Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Bake 1 hour, covered in a 350° oven.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into buttered casserole dish. Top with crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Freezes well.

title: chocolate milk shake
directions: Place ice cream in a blender container.
Add milk and chocolate.
Cover.
Blend until mixture is smooth.
Pour into glasses.
Serve immediately.
Makes about 4 (6 ounce) servings.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Mix juice with pudding mix.
Add fruit, whipped topping, marshmallows and nuts.
Chill before serving.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach for a few minutes.
Add a little salt.
Drain very well, get as much water out as possible.
Mix all ingredients together.
Make this 24 hours before serving.
Refrigerate.
Scoop out inside of bread.
Add dip mixture.
Place pieces of bread and Townhouse cookies around bread.

title: english butter toffee bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

Butter a 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Arrange saltines right side up in a single layer on bottom of pan. Melt butter and sugar in medium-sized saucepan over medium heat. Bring to a boil; boil 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour over crackers and spread evenly with spatula.
Bake for 5 minutes (if crackers shift, rearrange with fork).

title: bran apple muffins
directions: If all-purpose	flour
is used, use 1 tablespoon baking powder and 1/2 teaspoon salt.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients until boils up, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Add the jello and dissolve.
Whip the chilled Pet milk until stiff. Fold into jello mixture.
Put in vanilla crumb crust.

title: easy camp stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook in crock-pot all day. Make sure potatoes and butter beans are done.

title: cranberry cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a small bowl, combine crumbs, pecans and butter.
In the bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan, firmly press crumb mixture. Bake until golden, 5 to 6 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool slightly.
Spread with cranberry sauce; set aside.

title: egg rolls
directions: Mix all together (except wraps) and drain again for a couple of hours.
Mix together cornstarch and water to make a thin paste. Lay 1 wrap so that it looks like a diamond shape.
Place about 2 tablespoons of the mixture in the center of the wrap.
Fold up the bottom corner.
Brush cornstarch on seams.
Fold sides to center. Roll up from the bottom and make sure flap seals.
Fry in hot deep fat until crisp and brown.

title: birthday punch
directions: Place sherbet in punch bowl.
Pour ginger ale over sherbet. Mix.
Sherbet will melt to make a thick, foamy punch.

title: fudge
directions: Cook sugar, cocoa, salt and milk on medium-high heat until soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, margarine and nuts.
Stir until right consistency.
Drop on wax paper with spoon.

title: bread sticks
directions: Cut each slice of bread into 5 sticks (cut crust off).
Place on cookie sheet; bake for 1 hour at 200°.
Place crusts in same oven.
When time is up, crush finely the toasted crusts.
Heat peanut butter and oil; do not cook.
Holding toasted bread sticks with tongs, dip each stick into peanut butter mixture; allow to dry well.
Roll in crumb mixture and place on wax paper.

title: potato dumplings
directions: The day before you need the dumplings, wash and boil 1 pound and 10 ounces of potatoes; peel while still hot and mash, then leave them to cool.
The next day, rub them through a fine sieve. Grate the raw potatoes; put them into a cloth and squeeze out as much liquid as possible.
Combine the cooked, mashed potatoes with the raw, grated potatoes and knead into them the egg, flour and salt.
With floured hands, shape the mixture into dumplings about the size of your fist.
Drop into boiling, salted water and simmer until done.
Cooking time:
about 20 minutes.

title: larry's green tomatoes
directions: Combine the vinegar, water and salt and boil for 5 minutes. Cut tomatoes to a desired size and put into Mason jars.
Fill jars with boiling vinegar-water mixture to 1/2-inch from top.
Seal and wait 4 to 6 weeks before using.

title: praline snackers
directions: Arrange graham crackers in a single layer in a foil-lined 15 x 10-inch baking pan.
In a saucepan, bring butter and brown sugar to a boil; cook and stir just until sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Pour evenly over crackers; sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with marshmallows; bake 3 to 5 minutes longer or until top is bubbly and marshmallows are lightly browned.
Drizzle with chocolate syrup.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Break into squares.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: In skillet cook sausage until brown; drain off fat.
Separate rolls into 8 triangles.
Place in ungreased 12-inch pizza pan with points toward center.
Press over bottom and up sides; seal. Spoon on the sausage, then potatoes, then Cheddar.
In a bowl beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over crust.
Sprinkle on Parmesan.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sage cornbread dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir well.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: round steak with stove top stuffing
directions: Brown the round steak in a pan, then place the meat in a square pan.
Place the prepared Stove Top stuffing onto the meat, then fold over, making it one rounded piece.
Place pieces of bacon, mushrooms and onions on top of the meat.
Pour 1 can of beef broth over the top of the meat.
Cover with foil; bake at least 2 hours at 350°.
Slice and serve.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream the eggs, sugars and oil.
Add vanilla and zucchini. Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture. Fold in nuts. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 large loaves or 6 small loaves.

title: graham balls
directions: Grind crackers in food processor.
In a mixing bowl stir with a wooden spoon the softened butter with the powdered sugar for 1 minute until soft.
Mix the ground crackers with the butter mixture and egg.
Spread coconut all over a sheet of wax paper. Roll the mixture into balls and then roll into coconut until the ball is fully covered.
Refrigerate for better taste.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute onion in 2 teaspoons butter until slightly brown. Add potatoes
and
just
enough
water	to cover.
Cook until potatoes are
tender.
Melt
remaining butter;
blend in with flour, salt, pepper and celery salt.
Add enough milk to make a thin
paste. Add potatoes and onion and add remaining milk. Reheat.
Do not boil. Sprinkle with parsley and serve.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Boil water, sugar and cornstarch to medium thickness.
Add jello and sliced strawberries.
Stir well.
Pour into baked pie shell and chill for 3 or 4 hours.

title: blintzes souffle
directions: Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put all ingredients in blender and pour over blintzes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: savory stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms; finely chop 1/4 c. stems.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Place chicken, celery and onion in 9 x 13-inch casserole. Layer mushrooms over top of chicken mixture.
Mix together soups and sour cream.
Pour over top of mushrooms and chicken.
Prepare stuffing mix according to package directions and crumble over top of casserole.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: drop sand tarts with nuts
directions: Add 1/2 teaspoon almond extract to change flavor.

title: cool whip melba
directions: Put peaches in a blender and puree.
Add 3 tablespoons juice and 1/2 cup sugar and mix well.
Put into greased Cool Whip container layering as you go (bang on table to get air bubbles out).
Optional:
Add jelly or fruits to layers if you wish. Freeze for 24 hours.
Unmold and garnish.
Leftovers must be returned to freezer.

title: chocolate candy
directions: Mix and bring to boil.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Set in sink of cold water and stir until thick enough to pour into buttered dish.

title: chicken and broccoli curry(serves 6 to 8)
directions: In a greased casserole dish, layer chicken and broccoli (slightly thawed).
Make a sauce by stirring together canned soup, mayonnaise, curry powder, lemon juice and white wine.
Pour over top of broccoli and chicken.
Spread grated cheese over the top. Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: chicken salad croissants
directions: Toss together the chicken, celery and pineapple.
Blend mayonnaise, lemon juice, onion flakes, seasoned salt and lemon pepper.
Stir into chicken mixture along with nuts, if desired. Mound on croissant and top with alfalfa sprouts.
Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and chill until ready to serve.

title: noodles and sausage casserole
directions: Mix onion and meat together; fry until slightly brown, then add soup and one can of water.
Mix well.
Cook noodles until tender.
Add to onion mixture.
Put in casserole.
Cover with the cheese.
Bake until golden brown.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and eat.
Better the second day.

title: creamy cheese cake
directions: Beat together sugar and cheese.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Pour into spring-form pan, dusted with graham cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool for 1 hour.
Top with jam or canned pie filling.

title: fiesta dip
directions: Brown ground beef; add all ingredients except cheese and olives.
When cooked, put in serving bowl and top with cheese, olives and salsa.
Serve with tortilla chips on Ritz crackers.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together.
Cook in loaf pans 55 minutes in a 325° oven. Enjoy!
For a nice moist bread, your bananas must be "overly ripe."

title: apple muffins
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together. Add liquid ingredients and mix until smooth. Add apples. Divide into muffin tins.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: one pot dinner(a man pleaser)
directions: Brown ground beef and bacon with onions until onions are transparent.
Drain off fat.
Combine all ingredients in crock-pot and cook on low 4 to 6 hours or can be simmered on stove for one hour or longer.

title: potato casserole
directions: Beat first five ingredients at medium speed until blended, then at high speed until fluffy. Spoon into greased baking dish. Spread onion rings over top. Bake at 300° for 35 minutes.

title: seeded yellow corn crisps
directions: Make several days ahead or early in the day on which you plan to serve.
Start heating oven to 350°.
Sift corn meal with flour, salt and baking soda, stir in shortening, milk and poppy seed.
On a lightly floured surface, knead dough 6 to 8 times or until it just holds together.

Break off nickel-size pieces; with rolling pin roll each into a very thin 4-inch round, leaving edges ragged. Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet 15 minutes, or until golden. Just before serving, brush crisps with melted butter, sprinkle with salt.
Makes 24.

title: fudge
directions: In saucepan, combine milk, sugar, and marshmallows.
Bring to boil.
Boil slowly for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
In a bowl, place chocolate chips, butter, and nuts.
Pour cooked ingredients over ingredients in bowl.
Mix well until butter melts and chips melt.
Pour into a greased pan and let cool.
Cut into desired size squares.

title: broccoli pie
directions: Cook broccoli and onion about 10 minutes.
Drain.
Add chicken and cheese.
Put in greased pie pan.
Mix Bisquick, milk, salt, pepper and eggs.
Pour over broccoli mixture.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Add extra cheese topping during last 5 minutes. Let cool for 5 minutes before cutting.

title: cherry tomato poppers
directions: Cut cherry tomatoes in half. Mix minced garlic, oregano, parsley, salt and pepper and oil in a large mixing bowl. Add cut tomatoes and mix gently with clean hands to coat tomato halves. Place on cookie baking sheet with the cut side up. Bake in low temperature oven, 175° to 195°, for 2 to 4 hours. Be careful, they can dehydrate too far. After the first 1.5 hours of cooking, check every 30 minutes for desired consistency. Serve warm on toast points, crackers or crispy French bread.

title: cottage cheese stollen
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs. Melt butter.
Add to dry ingredients.
Add cottage cheese, then add rest of ingredients.
Forms 2 stollens.
Bake on greased cookie sheet in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: fudge
directions: Cook until reaches soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and pour into buttered dish.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: beans, tomato and pepper salad
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees, in a large bowl, toss spicy seasoning and 1 Tbsp. Olive oil with cherry tomatoes and pepper. Spread on baking sheet and roast for 25 minutes. Combine roasted vegetables, drained beans, parsley and remaining olive oil in a salad bowl.

title: spinach soup(spinatsuppe)
directions: Wash fresh spinach, then chop coarsely.
If frozen spinach is used, defrost and drain.
Bring chicken stock to a boil and add spinach.
Simmer 6 to 8 minutes.
Strain soup and remove spinach. Chop finely and reserve until later.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour and add hot stock, a little at a time. Return saucepan to heat and bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Add spinach and seasoning and simmer 5 minutes.
Garnish with quartered eggs.

title: sweet sauce for apple pie
directions: In heavy 2-quart saucepan over low heat, with wire whisk, beat egg yolks, sugar and salt.
Gradually stir in milk; cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and coats the back of spoon, about 25 minutes.
Stir in vanilla.
Serve warm or cold over apple pie.

title: potato patties
directions: Peel and quarter enough potatoes to fill a casserole bowl. Sprinkle heavily with seasoned steak seasoning.
Pour melted butter over the potatoes.
Cover and bake at 350° until they are fork-tender, about 45 minutes.

title: oven stew
directions: Spread beef in bottom of large casserole dish or roaster.
Salt and pepper meat.
Cover with vegetables.
Pour the V-8 vegetable juice over all.
Add water to cover meat and vegetables.
Mix tapioca and sugar.
Sprinkle over top and "puddle" to moisten it. Cover and place in a 325° to 350° oven.
Bake about 5 hours. Frozen peas added the last 1/2 hour will add color and flavor.
Be sure to leave "head" room in pan for bubbling.

title: 9 layer dip
directions: In a crescent dish, cover the bottom with refried beans.
Top with 2 ounces of grated Cheddar; melt cheese.
Layer green onions, seasoned sour cream, black olives, Jack cheese, diced tomatoes and cilantro on top of one another.
Warm in the oven or broiler just until cheese begins to melt.
Serve with Tostado chips or chips of choice.

title: wesson oil french dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and blend well.
Add garlic salt if you like.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix flour, salt and sugar.
Add corn, milk and eggs. Pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with butter.
Bake 1 hour in 400° oven.
Center should be firm.
Check after 45 minutes to see if center is firm.

title: corn casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, melt oleo.
When melted, add corn and sprinkle corn meal mix over the top.
Mix lightly in the pan. Bake 1 hour at 350° or until lightly brown.

title: mexican hot corn bread
directions: Mix and bake in an 8 3/4 x 8 3/4-inch pan or a square pan at 450°.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Place in well-greased baking pan and bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate treats
directions: Melt and keep hot chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
Add chow mein noodles and walnuts.
Mix well and drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper to cool.

title: upside-down ham loaf
directions: Combine eggs, milk, onion, mustard, cayenne and bread crumbs. Add ham, mixing well.
Melt butter in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Sprinkle sugar over butter.
Arrange pineapple on top of sugar. Press ham mixture into pan.
Bake in moderately hot oven at 375° for 45 minutes. Turn ham loaf out, upside down, on hot platter. Makes 6 servings.

title: i only eat
directions: Spread peanut butter to middle of one slice of bread.
Add honey to other side of bread.
Cut not fold bread in half.
Close together.
Serve on bear plate.

title: chicken green bean casserole
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine soup, milk and salt; stir until blended.
Fold in chicken, green beans, chop suey vegetables, onion and cheese.
Turn into casserole and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Top with onion rings and bake 10 more minutes.

title: french onion pie
directions: Fill frozen crust with 1 1/2 cups fried onion rings; reserve remaining 1/2 cup for garnish.
Beat eggs slightly; add milk, 1/2 cup cheese, salt and cayenne.
Pour over onions in pie shell. Sprinkle with 1 cup cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes. Sprinkle reserved onions around edge of pie.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes longer.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: authentic mexican pralines
directions: Put 2 cups sugar, water, pecans and salt in pan; bring to a boil.
In meantime, brown 1/2 cup sugar in a small iron skillet; let it melt and get to light caramel color.
Pour into first mixture and continue to cook until it forms a ball when dropped in cold water.
Add butter and beat until it cools and thickens a little; drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper, which has been laid over newspaper.
When cool and hard, candy will lift easily from paper.

title: quick german fruit cobbler
directions: Mix all dry
ingredients
together.
Beat
egg and pour over dry ingredients.
Mix
to
make a crumb mixture.
Sweeten fruit to taste and
add
some
water if it is not juicy.
Pour into a buttered
x 11 1/2-inch pan.
Sprinkle crumb mixture over fruit mixture.
Melt butter and pour over entire mixture. Bake at 400° for
about
minutes
or until crust is golden brown.
Suitable for freezing.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together except butter; then melt butter and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shells and bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Done when a knife comes out clean.

title: fresh corn and vegetable pot
directions: Cut
corn
from cob into casserole. Slice tomatoes into 1/4 inch slices.
Trim ends from zucchini and slice lengthwise into about
pieces.
Add
tomatoes and zucchini as well as separated onion rings.
Add spices and mix vegetables carefully.
Dot
with butter, cover and bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Serves 8.

title: pizza casserole
directions: In a skillet, brown beef and onion until beef is no longer pink and onion is tender.
Drain any fat.
Add all remaining ingredients; spoon into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: beef roast-brisket
directions: Beef Roast:
Put a 3 to 4-pound roast on piece of foil large enough to wrap meat.
Pour mushroom soup, onion soup mix and A.1. sauce over roast.
Wrap in foil (seal) and bake at 275° for 4 hours or at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Use juice as gravy over meat.

title: easy dessert
directions: Place cinnamon rolls on foil or in cake pan.
Cover with cherry pie filling, brown sugar and pecans.
Bake in oven at 350 degrees until hot and bubbly.

title: orange jello pound cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs and oil with hand held beater; set aside. Mix Jell-O and cold water.
Combine ingredients; mix with hand held beater.
Place in Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fresh rhubarb pie
directions: Cut rhubarb into 1-inch pieces.
In mixing bowl, combine sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in rhubarb.
Toss gently to coat fruit.
Let set 15 minutes.
Pour into pie dish lined with pastry. Dot with butter or oleo; slit top crust.
Place over mixture; flute and trim edges.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Remove foil from around the edge of pie and continue baking for 25 more minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm or cool on rack before serving.
Top each serving with vanilla ice cream if desired.

title: pasta in a pot
directions: Cook beef in a little oil in a large deep pan until brown, stirring often.
Drain off fat.
Add onion, garlic, spaghetti sauce, tomatoes and drained mushrooms.
Mix well.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: cranberry nut pie
directions: Mix berries, 1/2 cup sugar and nuts together and put in pie shell.
In mixing bowl, mix flour, eggs, sugar and butter and pour over berries.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: pecan-topped coffee cake
directions: Cream butter;
gradually
add
cup sugar and 1/2 cup brown sugar,
beating
well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well. Stir
in
vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Add to cream mixture alternately
with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture; mix well after each addition.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 13
x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine pecans, 1/2 cup brown sugar
and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon; stir well and sprinkle over batter.
Cover and chill 8 to 10 hours.
Uncover batter, let come
to
room temperature.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Yields 15 servings.

title: barbecuen der steak marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a plastic bag.
Put in refrigerator 3 to 4 hours, turning meat here and there.
Then let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes before grilling.
Baste on grill.

title: iced tea
directions: Boil 2 quarts water in microwave for 12 to 15 minutes. Add tea bags and let steep for about 10 minutes. Pour into gallon container. Add water to tea bags and let steep about 5 minutes. Add to pitcher along with lemonade and sugar. Fill with enough water to make a gallon.

title: joan's vegetable soup
directions: Saute pureed onion and garlic in 3 tablespoons oil. Add tomato juice, chicken broth and other ingredients except potatoes. Simmer one hour. Add sliced potatoes and simmer another hour.

title: baked curried fruit
directions: Drain all fruit well.
Pour into 12 x 8 or 9 x 9-inch casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: picnic pork fry(laci pecsenye)
directions: Sprinkle pork butts with salt and pepper.
Add paprika and garlic. Let stand for about 10 minutes.
Fry in deep fat.
Serve on slices of rye bread with sauerkraut.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Cook sugar, egg, butter, milk and salt approximately 3 to 4 minutes.
In this mixture, put nuts, cracker crumbs and coconut; pour on graham crackers.
Add another layer of whole graham crackers.
For icing, just powdered sugar icing.

title: shortbread
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add powdered sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour (mixture will be stiff).
Press into bottom of 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Prick dough with fork.
Chill 30 minutes.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Cook cornbread and let cool.
Crumble on bottom of greased large casserole.
Add Pepperidge Farm stuffing.
Meanwhile, saute onion and celery in margarine.
Add to mixture.
Add turkey gravy to 2 cups water and chicken bouillon.
Add poultry seasoning to gravy and pour over dressing.
Cook 30 minutes or longer, until right texture.
Do not let it get too dry.
Cover with foil (you may need more liquid).

title: dirt dessert
directions: You will also need an 8-inch clay colored pot.

title: creamy chocolate layered pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon of milk and sugar in a large bowl with a wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in 1 1/2 cups of the Cool Whip.
Spread on bottom of crust.

title: beef and noodles
directions: Cut meat into cubes.
In a large saucepan brown half of the meat in hot oil.
Remove the meat from the pan.
Brown the remaining meat with onion and garlic (if desired).
Drain fat. Return all meat to pan.
Stir in beef broth, vinegar, and pepper. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, simmer for 1 hour.
Stir noodles into broth mixture.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Drain meat and noodles.
Reserve 2 1/2 cups of the liquid.
Return liquid to pan.
Stir together 1/4 cup beef broth and flour.
Stir into mixture in pan.
Cook and stir till thickened and bubbly.
Stir in beef and noodles.
Heat thoroughly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: turgetti
directions: Boil
spaghetti
and
drain.
Add
turkey and all other ingredients.
Put grated cheese on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Cut angel food cake into bite size chunks in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together powdered sugar, butter and egg yolks; beat until fluffy.
Whip in Cool Whip and pour over cake.
Crush Butterfinger bars and put on top.
Better if left to set overnight.

title: chocolate brittle
directions: Mix butter, sugar and water.
Cook over low heat until candy thermometer reaches 290°.
Pour on two buttered pizza pans. Spread to edge of pan.
Cover with melted chocolate and press nuts on top.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: strawberry angel dessert
directions: Dissolve jello, sugar and salt in boiling water.
Add frozen berries while mix is hot.
Set in refrigerator and let it begin to thicken.
When partly jelled, fold in Dream Whip.
Line long pan or casserole with pinched off pieces of angel food cake.
Place these tight together and pour strawberry mixture over cake.
Let set in refrigerator.
Can be topped with Dream Whip, boiled custard.

title: fried rice
directions: Saute onions, celery and pork in oil until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Do not overcook.
Add rice and bean sprouts which have been rinsed with cold water and drained.
Combine egg and soy sauce.
Stir into rice mixture.
Cook, stirring 2 to 3 minutes or until heated.
Season to taste.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Butter large rectangular Pyrex dish.
Layer with crushed corn flakes (1/2).
Mix all ingredients, except soup and cheese, and pour into dish.
Cover with undiluted soup.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Top with remaining 1/2 of corn flakes; dot with butter. Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: kansas cucumber salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar and dill; mix well.
Add cucumbers and onions; toss.
Cover and chill for at least 1 hour.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: dixie hen house eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant and dice.
Cook in salted water until just tender.
Drain and set aside.
Cook sausage in skillet until well done.
Drain on paper towels.
Saute green onions, onions and celery in skillet until transparent.
Prepare stuffing mix according to package directions.
Combine eggplant, sausage, onion mixture, salt, pepper and stuffing mix.
Transfer to a shallow baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted. Makes 12 servings.

title: top of the stove rice pudding
directions: Cook rice, covered, until done.
Add other ingredients, except vanilla and nutmeg.
Cook on medium heat, stirring all the time, until raisins are plump and pudding is thick.
Add vanilla and sprinkle some nutmeg (according to taste).
Stir together and refrigerate.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Mix together cocoa and oats.
Cook sugar, margarine and milk for 1 minute at rolling boil.
Add peanut butter and vanilla to mixture.
Beat well.
Add oats and cocoa.
Spoon onto pans to cool.

title: mushroom pie casserole
directions: Mix all together in a baking dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° until rice is fluffed.
May need to add more broth or water if dry (usually 1/4 cup).

title: make ahead casserole
directions: Combine ingredients in a baking dish.
Refrigerate overnight and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
This recipe may be cut in half.

title: crabbies
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on split muffins.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
When frozen, put in Ziploc bag and keep until ready to serve.

title: caramel chocolate bars
directions: Combine caramels and 1/3 cup milk; set aside.

Combine cake mix, 3/4 cup butter and remaining milk until smooth. Put 1/2 mixture into 9 x 13 pan. Bake 6 minutes. Cool. Pour melted caramels over cake layer. Add chocolate chips and 1/2 of walnuts. Mix. Add remaining walnuts and cake mix. Run knife through several times to marbleize. Bake at 350° in 13 x 9 x 2 pan for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs and cherry fruit filling.
Mix well with electric mixer.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
When cooled, frost with can of chocolate frosting mix.

title: country chicken chowder
directions: Saute onion in butter or margarine just until soft in a medium size saucepan.
Stir in soup, water, chicken, corn, evaporated milk and pepper; heat just to boiling.
Pour into heated soup bowls.
Sprinkle with parsley if you wish.

title: ham and cheese casserole
directions: Make cream sauce using butter, flour and milk.
Add salt and desired seasonings.
Add soup and Cheez Whiz.
Saute scallions and add.
Thaw peas.
Add ham and peas to cream sauce mixture.
Cook linguine (broken in half) in salted water and drain.
Combine noodles with sauce mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or heat in microwave.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of celery soup

title: chicken piccata
directions: Beat egg with 1 tablespoon lemon juice in small bowl. In medium bowl, combine flour, garlic, paprika, salt and pepper. Dip chicken in egg mixture, then in flour mixture. In large skillet, brown chicken in margarine. Dissolve bouillon in boiling water. Add remaining lemon juice and pour over chicken. Simmer 20 to 40 minutes in covered skillet, moving it around occasionally with spatula to avoid sticking. Enjoy!

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix well with hands.
Roll in foil and cure 24 hours in refrigerator.
Leave in foil.
Place into pan and pour 1-inch of water in pan. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: chicken-broccoli bake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together in large bowl.
In large 10 x 15-inch pan, put broccoli.
Place boneless chicken breasts on top of broccoli.
Pour soup mixture over chicken and broccoli.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Take out; spread grated Cheddar cheese on top and return to oven until melted.
Serve over rice.

title: crisp pecan cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening, add well beaten eggs; add dry ingredients and nuts.
Drop from teaspoon about 2-inches apart. Bake at 300° to 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: jalapeno rice
directions: Mix onion, sour cream and chiles well with rice.
Layer rice, Jack cheese, rice.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in greased casserole. Sprinkle Cheddar on top last 10 minutes of cooking.
Serves 10.

title: rice and beef oriental
directions: Saute beef in oil in large skillet until browned about 3 to 5 minutes.
Add vegetables and stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add water, soy sauce and seasoning mix.
Bring to a full boil.
Stir in rice. Cover; remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork. Makes 4 servings.

title: 12 hour salad
directions: Shred lettuce into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Layer lettuce, peppers, onion and peas.
Mix mayonnaise and sour cream; spread on top.
Sprinkle sugar, cheese and bacon on top.
Cover and refrigerate about 4 to 8 hours.
Do not toss until ready to serve.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake at 325° for about 15 to 20 minutes. Cut into squares.

title: coconut pie
directions: Melt butter in saucepan. Add milk. Mix flour and sugar together and add to butter and milk, then add vanilla. Cook until it thickens. Put in baked pie shell. Beat egg whites with a little sugar. Add to pie and bake in oven at 350° until whites are brown.

title: creamy chicken-broccoli rice
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine soup, water and pepper.
Over medium-high heat, heat to boiling.
Stir in rice.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover.
Cook 25 minutes or until rice is tender and mixture is creamy, stirring often.
tags: cream of chicken and broccoli soup

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix yeast, water and sugar.
Let rest 10 minutes.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut shortening into flour mixture.
Add just enough extra flour to roll out.
Roll into 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into circles and place in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pans.
Brush with melted butter and let rise for 30 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes or until done.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: hamburger and potato casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onions until done.
Drain grease. Combine this mixture with other ingredients and mix well.
Put into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Always a hit! Quick and easy for those who work!!! Children love it!!

title: braunschweiger spread
directions: Mix well.
Chill several hours in serving dish.

title: cherry bites
directions: Combine biscuit mix, eggs, milk and sugar.
Beat until smooth. Pour into 12 greased 1 1/2-inch muffin cups.
Spoon 1 tablespoon pie filling into each cup.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden.
Remove from oven and cool.
Fill center of each with remaining pie filling.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: chicken noodle tetrazzini
directions: Cook chicken in water and salt until tender.
Remove from broth, bone and cut in small pieces.
Take fat from broth and use 1 quart of broth.
Cook noodles in broth with lid off after it starts boiling.
Cook according to directions on noodle package.

title: peachy squash
directions: Saute onion in margarine until soft.
Add sliced squash and peaches.
Cover and simmer on low heat about 15 minutes, until squash is crisp and tender.
Stir occasionally and season.

title: coney island sauce
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain off fat.
Add rest of ingredients and cook for 10 minutes.
Great for hot dogs!

title: stir-fry chicken fajitas
directions: Wrap tortillas in aluminum foil.
Place them in the oven and heat to 350°.
Sprinkle the chicken pieces with salt and cumin. Slice the pepper and onion into thin slices.
Coat a large nonstick skillet with vegetable spray and place over medium-high heat.
Add the bell pepper and onion and stir-fry for 3 minutes.
Add chicken and garlic and stir-fry for 3 to 4 minutes.
Next, add the salsa and cook until heated through.
Spoon mixture in center of tortilla.
Sprinkle with cilantro.
Fold in half.
Serve with sour cream.

title: mother's molasses pies
directions: Cook in pie crusts until done.
(This makes two pies.)

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown hamburger and put in all ingredients.
Simmer for about one hour or until vegetables are cooked.
Can add potatoes, if desired.

title: butterscotch pecan roll
directions: Melt chips in milk in the top of a double boiler.
When chips are dissolved, add pecans and stir real good.
Roll into a roll in
either
foil or wax paper.
Cool and then cut into slices.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt almond bark in Dutch oven in oven at 250° until soft. Add peanut butter, vanilla and Rice Krispies.
Put in buttered dish until firm.

title: shish kabob
directions: In a bowl, stir together first 5 ingredients to make marinade. Place steak cubes in a large, shallow pan.
Pour marinade over steak and stir to coat.
Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours, stir occasionally.
Oil 12 long skewers.
Skewer meat alternately with vegetables, beginning and ending with meat.
Broil or grill for about 20 minutes.
Brush with marinade while cooking.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: kitchen potpourri
directions: Stir once a day for 2 weeks.
Keep in airtight container.

title: chocolate sauerkraut cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Set aside.
Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Mix well and then add vanilla, salt and cocoa.
Mix well.
Alternately add flour mixture and water.
Add kraut.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients until well blended.
Grease iron skillet or bread pans.
Pour mixture into hot prepared skillet.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: quiche with meat
directions: Fry and drain hamburger/sausage.
Combine ingredients and pour into shells.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter.
Mix mayonnaise and juice in large bowl. Add chicken and all ingredients except croutons.
Mix well. Salt and pepper to taste.
Place in an 8 x 11-inch baking dish. Top with croutons. Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: skroodle salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar and milk and toss with onion, pepper and noodles.
Set overnight in refrigerator.

title: nut macaroons
directions: Mix and drop on well greased sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until dry around edge at 350°.

title: chow chow
directions: Grind all vegetables together in food processor for fine chop or hand chop for coarse chop (recommend hand chop all tomatoes and red pepper).
Add other ingredients and cook on medium heat to bring to a boil, then boil on low heat for 30 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 quarts.

title: frito-chili pie
directions: Layer bottom of pan with chips.
Mix all other ingredients except cheese.
Melt in saucepan.
Layer on top of chips.
Sprinkle cheese on top and melt in 350° oven.

title: sweet potato chiffon
directions: Combine the first 3 items
and press in 9 x 13 x 2
inch pan. Set aside.
Beat the next 3 items until fluffy and spread over the crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, then cool.
Mix the pudding with milk and beat 2 minutes.
Add the cooked sweet potatoes and dash of cinnamon to the pudding mixture.
Fold.
Cool Whip into mixture.
Pour over cream cheese mixture and sprinkle pecans over top.

title: cheese soup
directions: In a large stock pot, add chicken broth to vegetables and butter.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Add milk and cheese over low heat.
Combine flour, cornstarch and water, stirred together.
Add to first mixture and continue to stir until smooth and thick.
Do not have heat too high or soup will stick.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: flicky bohemian ham and noodles
directions: Boil noodles according to package directions.
Butter dish thickly.
Layer noodles and ham alternately, ending with noodles. Beat yolks and milk together.
Pour over top and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until brown.

title: velveeta mostaccioli
directions: Cook hamburger, spaghetti sauce, tomatoes, tomato paste and salt and pepper
for
15 minutes.
Cook and drain noodles. Put layer of noodles
in
large baking dish, greased.
Add 1/2 of the spaghetti sauce.
Put
on
to
slices
of cheese. Repeat layers of
noodles,
spaghetti
sauce and cheese.
This time put cheese
under
sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Marinate for 24 hours, turning 2 to 3 times.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions in 13 x 9-inch pan. Let cake cool completely.
Divide the cake in half.
Break the first half up into small pieces and put in the bottom of a punch bowl.
Make the pudding mix with 5 cups milk.
Pour half of the pudding mix over the cake, then layering, add half of the pie filling, 1 can of the crushed pineapple and half of the bananas. Mix the whipped topping and nuts together.
Put half of this over the layers.
Repeat the layers ending with nut topping.
Decorate with the cherries and nuts if desired.
Refrigerate for at least 4 hours.

title: gratin of potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel the potatoes and slice them thinly.
Lay the slices slightly overlapping in a large baking dish, greased with the butter.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all together except shortening, which add last.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 300° for 45 minutes to one hour.
(Insert toothpick which should come out clean.)

title: braden's cookies
directions: Cream the butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, salt, cream of tartar and soda; mix well.
Add chopped nuts.
Form dough into a roll about 8 inches long and 2 inches in diameter.
Roll up with wax paper.
Chill until firm.
Cut into thin slices and bake 10 to 12 minutes in a preheated 375° oven.

title: vegetable fried rice
directions: Cook rice and set aside.
Add oil to skillet.
When hot (medium), add vegetables.
Stir constantly until cooked.
Add rice, soy sauce (desired amount of soy sauce) and seasonings. Enjoy!

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add garden Ragu mix to meat and eggplant in casserole dish.
Layer eggplant, meat and cheese.

title: scalloped corn
directions: In a saucepan, combine corn and milk. Heat through.
Gradually stir in egg. Add 1 cup crumbs, onion, pimiento, salt and pepper. Mix well.
Pour into a greased 1-quart baking dish. Combine 1/2 cup crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle over corn. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix onion, margarine and cottage cheese in a large bowl.
Add and mix, one at a time, the boxes of corn bread mix.
Beat eggs in, one at a time.
Add and stir in broccoli with all its juice. Bake at 400° for 40 minutes in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Cook in microwave or saute in skillet.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, cheese and lemon juice together.
Layer broccoli, chicken and cheese mixture.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in a 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
May be served alone or over rice.

title: baked zucchini
directions: Cook zucchini until tender.
Drain well.
Mix other ingredients.
Add zucchini and bake 30 minutes in 400° oven.

title: heavenly cheese mold
directions: Dissolve
gelatin in boiling water.
Add juices.
Chill until slightly
thickened.
Fold in drained pineapple, cheese and whipped cream.
Pour into 1 1/2 cup mold.
Luscious!

title: mexican-style snapper with lime
directions: In a large skillet, saute green onions in butter until tender. Also, saute minced garlic if using fresh.
Add tomatoes, chilies, parsley, salt, garlic salt, lime peel and black pepper; mix well. Bring mixture to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Add snapper to skillet; spoon sauce over fillets.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork. Serve garnished with lime wedges.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix, in large Tupperware Fix, 3/4 cup of sugar with 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Cut biscuits in quarters and add to sugar and cinnamon. Put top on bowl, let air out and shake up and down until biscuits are covered.
Put mixture in Bundt pan, well-greased and floured evenly.
Melt 1 1/2 sticks of butter, 1 cup of sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon; spoon over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk until it thickens.

In a separate bowl, put vanilla wafers on bottom, then slice bananas to cover vanilla wafers, then pour pudding over the vanilla wafers and bananas. Then top with vanilla wafers and bananas like on the bottom.

title: pea salad
directions: Drain each can and put vegetables in a bowl.
Heat to boiling 1/2 cup vinegar, 3/4 cup sugar and 1/2 cup salad oil.
Cool slightly.
Pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate 2 hours or overnight.
Keeps well in refrigerator 2 weeks or longer.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Line the bottom of a 9 x 11-inch casserole dish with strips of uncooked bacon.
Cover bacon with 1 box of Minute rice.
Wash and salt chicken; lay pieces on top of rice.
Mix together the soup, water and seasonings; pour over chicken and rice.
Wrap the dish in foil and bake for 2 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: carrots with lemon juice
directions: Scrub carrots and cut into matchstick size pieces.
Place in oven proof dish with lid.
Pour butter-lemon mixture over carrots. Cover and bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: grill baked apple-ginger cakes
directions: You will also need 8 to 10-inch squares foil.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Beat eggs well; stir in pineapple and juice.
Add vanilla, sifted flour, salt and soda.
Mix all together.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: easy tater tot casserole
directions: Mix soup and milk; place ingredients in layers topping with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
This is a quick delicious meal.

title: divinity candy(heritage recipe)
directions: Mix well,
2 c. white sugar, syrup, water and 1 tsp. vanilla, and cook until it reaches 250 degrees on candy thermometer.

title: creole cabbage
directions: Saute green pepper, celery and onion in butter in a large skillet.
Add remaining ingredients; cover and simmer for about 10 minutes, or until tender.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: oatmeal icebox cookies
directions: Blend oleo, sugar and eggs.
Add flour and remaining ingredients.
Form into rolls; wrap in wax paper and refrigerate overnight.
Slice thin and bake on ungreased sheet at 350° for ten minutes.
May also be frozen.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: Using mixer at medium speed, beat butter, sugar and salt for 2 minutes.
Blend in flour at low speed until a smooth dough forms. Spray pan with cooking spray.
Press dough into pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Wash and remove seeds and membrane from peppers.
In saucepan, add green peppers to boiling, salted water.
Boil 5 minutes; drain.
Sprinkle with salt inside.
Combine meat, rice and Worcestershire sauce together with tomatoes.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Stuff peppers with meat mixture; place peppers in baking dish upright and bake, uncovered, for 25 minutes at 350°.
May sprinkle with grated cheese if desired.

title: lisa's party punch
directions: Add water to frozen concentrates as directed on cans.
Mix all ingredients well.
Serve in punch bowl over ice.
Yield:
50 servings.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
In bottom of pan, layer coconut and nuts.
Prepare cake mix according to box directions and pour over coconut and nuts.

title: squaw bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Divide the dough into parts and shape each into round pone about the size of your skillet and 1/8-inch thick.
Fry the bread in about 1/4-inch hot cooking oil quicking until golden brown on each side.
Cut into wedges and serve hot. Delicious with butter, jams or other sweet spreads.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas and vanilla.
Set aside.
Mix eggs, brown sugar, sugar and oil.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in bananas. Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: asparagus with cheese and mushrooms
directions: Cook asparagus until done or follow directions on frozen food box.
Cook in boiling salted water 12 to 15 minutes or until stalks are tender.
Drain thoroughly.
Melt butter in pot; add mushrooms and cook until softened, about 5 minutes.
Remove from pan and set aside.
Add more butter to make 1/4 cup.
Add flour and blend.
Add milk.
Stirring constantly, cook until smooth and thickened.
Add cheese and stir until dissolved.
Add mushrooms; blend.
Divide into 6 portions; arrange asparagus on hot toast. Pour over cheese mixture.
Serve at once.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown and drain hamburger meat. Melt butter, add macaroni, coat macaroni, add hamburger, onion, salt, pepper, sugar and tomato juice. Turn down to simmer. When done turn off & cover with grated cheese.

title: fruit shake
directions: Place all ingredients in blender; cover.
Blend until smooth, about 1 to 2 minutes.

title: one pan turkey and stuffing
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Grease 10x6 or 11x7 pan.
Mix baking mix with milk, eggs, parsley, sage, thyme, salt, poultry seasoning, and pepper with a fork until batter is uniform (batter will be lumpy).
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake until golden brown and inserted knife comes out clean.

title: divinity
directions: Put sugar, karo syrup and water over medium heat.
Stir only until sugar is dissolved.
Cook to soft ball stage.
