Having beaten the egg whites, continue beating and add half the syrup (pour slowly into egg whites having a thin stream of syrup pouring into whites).
Continue beating while remaining syrup cooks to crack stage.
Pour remaining syrup into egg whites (same as before) and continue beating until thick enough to drop from spoon.

title: vinegar cookies
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugars thoroughly.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add vinegar and blend.
Sift flour and baking soda 4 times.
(It is important to sift 4 times; it makes them lighter.) Sift into the creamed mixture, a little at a time.
Add extracts and make into little balls.
Press flat with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in greased baking dish and dot with margarine.
Bake at 300°
until firm.

title: my favorite german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water and cool.
Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks one at a time, beating well after each addition (save whites for later).
Blend in vanilla and cooled chocolate mixture.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add alternately with buttermilk to chocolate mixture, beating well after each addition.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour in three 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Cool.

title: a love cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake in a warm oven.
Serve big slices daily.

title: dirt cups
directions: Pour the milk into a large bowl.
Add pudding mix and beat at low speed for 1 to 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Then stir in the Cool Whip and half of the crushed cookies.
Using remaining half of the cookies, place 1 tablespoon in the bottom of each of the 8 (7 ounce) plastic cups.
Fill the cups about 3/4 full with pudding mixture, then top with remaining cookies.
Refrigerate about 1 hour before serving.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Melt fat.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Add broth slowly to prevent lumping.
Add milk followed by all other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease bottom of 9x13 inch pan. Prepare and bake brownies following package directions for basic recipe. Remove from oven. Sprinkle marshmallows on hot brownies. Return to oven. Bake for three minutes longer. Place chocolate chips, peanut butter and butter in medium sauce pan. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until chips are melted. Add rice cereal; mix well. Spread mixture over marshmallow layer. Refrigerate until chilled. Cut into bars. Makes about 2 dozen (for special presentation, cut cookies into diamond shapes).

title: russian tea
directions: Combine all ingredients; store in a tightly covered container. Use 2 teaspoons of mix for each cup of boiling water.
One-third cup makes a quart of tea.

title: sugar-free pineapple pie
directions: Mix all together. Do not use recipe on cheesecake box.
Pour into 2 low-fat graham cracker crusts. Sprinkle with crumbs. Makes 2 pies.

title: lettuce and cauliflower salad
directions: Place in a 9 x 13 pan in the order in which they are listed. Refrigerate overnight and stir just before serving. Enjoy!

title: punch
directions: Mix all together, except water and freeze.
Pour 46 ounces of water over it.
Pour the ginger ale over it and mix up.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: country buttermilk dressing
directions: Mix together all ingredients; do not use blender.
Refrigerate a few hours.
Stir or shake well before serving.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Mix together flour, sugar and milk.
Pour over hot butter.
Pour berries over mixture. Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 8. Recipe can be halved.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Combine in one bowl.
Drop by teaspoonful into hot vegetable oil and fry like pancakes until golden brown.

title: texas hash
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer.
Serve with cornbread.

title: strawberry salad
directions: In medium saucepan, combine gelatin and pineapple with juice. Heat until all gelatin is dissolved.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, whip whipping cream with mixer about 2 minutes.
Fold in cottage cheese, cherries and gelatin mixture.
Place in an 8-inch square pan and refrigerate overnight.
Top with whipped cream and additional cherries before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Cream butter and sugar; add egg yolks and beat thoroughly.
Sprinkle flour over graham crackers; add baking powder and salt.
Add milk alternately.
Fold in egg whites; mix lightly and add nuts.
Bake in 2 greased and floured pans for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken cacciatore(servings: 4)
directions: Put the olive oil in a 5-quart Dutch oven.
Saute the garlic until soft; add the onion and peppers, all sliced very thin.
Add the sweet basil and oregano (more can be added if a more robust flavor is desired).
Add the white wine and bring to a simmer. Add the chicken and simmer until the meat is white, stirring occasionally.
Add the crushed tomatoes and simmer for 1 hour on very low heat.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Partially boil potatoes; cool and peel.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices; arrange in greased shallow baking dish.
Make a syrup of sugar, water and salt.
Add flavoring and margarine; pour over potatoes.
Cover and bake at 350° for about an hour.

title: deviled ham dip
directions: Mix together the cream cheese, Tabasco and mayonnaise.
Add mustard, deviled ham, onion and olives.
Refrigerate until serving time.
Makes about 2 1/4 cups.

title: apple muffins
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients into a bowl.
Blend in the next 3 ingredients.
Fold in last ingredient.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mexican pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta in boiling salted water 8-10 minutes, or until al dente.

title: corn creole
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion and celery and saute until tender (about 5 minutes).
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper and corn.
Cook until corn is tender.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: easy butterscotch squares
directions: In a medium saucepan, melt the butter, then add sugar, blending well.
Set aside to cool.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Blend flour and baking powder together, then add to mix.
Add vanilla and nuts, making sure to blend thoroughly.
Spread batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan; bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.
Check with cake tester to be sure it is completely baked.
While still warm, cut into squares and dust with confectioners sugar.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt morsels in saucepan over low heat.
Stir in peanuts and chow mein noodles.
Stir to mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Let cool.
Yield: 25 to 30 haystacks.

title: quick beef vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add all other ingredients except vegetables.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add vegetables.
Heat to boiling. Simmer 10 minutes or more.

title: delicate pineapple cake
directions: Make the cake mix as directed on package.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans.
Divide batter evenly in pans.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: apple cider crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel, core and slice apples into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Pour cider over apples.
Mix together flour, brown sugar, butter and cinnamon to make a crumbly pastry.
Sprinkle mixture over apples and bake 40 minutes.

title: golden west raisin pineapple sauce
directions: Heat butter, mustard and ginger until bubbly. Stir in jam. Add vinegar and 3/4 cup syrup from pineapple. Stir in cornstarch blended with water. Cook, stirring until thick, about 3 to 4 minutes. Add drained pineapple, raisins and cherries. Heat brandy and flame.

title: marinated grilled chicken
directions: Mix oil, vinegar, salt and poultry seasoning.
Bring to a boil.
Parboil chicken in sauce and allow to cool.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Grill and baste with remaining sauce.

title: crunchy punch
directions: Mix 9 cups boiling water with Jell-O.
Boil sugar and 4 cups water together and	cool.
Mix
with lemon juice.
Freeze pineapple juice in gallon
plastic	jugs.
When
ready
to use take from freezer 3 or 4
hours
before
time
to use.
Put in punch bowl.
Pour 2 large (32 ounce) bottles of 7-Up or ginger ale over this.	Mix so it
will
be
mushy.
Real good.
Punch bowl will not hold all at one time.
Use 7-Up accordingly.

title: crunchy banana muffins
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, oats, salt and baking soda.
Add honey, milk, egg white, oil and bananas.
Stir with fork just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: carrots hawaiian(from overrock inn)
directions: Cook all ingredients together and thicken with cornstarch.

title: molded shrimp salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add salt, vinegar and onion; chill until almost set.
Fold in shrimp, celery and green pepper.
Pour into molds and chill until firmly set.
Cut or turn out.
Serve on lettuce leaves with mayonnaise.

title: garlic and herb chicken
directions: Simply salt and pepper chicken.
Coat lightly with flour. Brown in skillet in oil.
Pour Hunt's sauce over chicken.
Simmer, covered, 20 minutes or until cooked through.

title: herb seasoning
directions: Combine herbs in small	bowl
and
mix	gently	with
a spoon. Divide into small jars.
Seal and label.
Use 1/2 to 1 teaspoon herb mixture for each quart of liquid you are seasoning.
Ideal for soups or stews.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: great grandma's sweet dill pickles
directions: Put pickles into a large bowl that can be covered. Sprinkle with celery seed.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat eggs together with sugar until light and well blended. Add oil; continue to beat.
Sift dry ingredients together and beat them into mixture.
Add pumpkin.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Turn onto a rack to cool.

title: new northland cookies(a refrigerator cookie without eggs)
directions: Mix shortening and brown sugar thoroughly.
Add water; mix well.
Sift together the dry ingredients and stir in.
Mix in desired nuts.
Mix thoroughly with hands.
Press into a smooth roll
2 1/2 inches in diameter.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Chill until stiff (several hours or overnight).
With thin, sharp knife, slice into thin slices, 1/8 to 1/16-inch thick.
Place a little apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until lightly browned at 400°, 6 to 8 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Combine margarine, peaches and 1 cup sugar.
Boil until mixture is dark.
Next, combine milk, vanilla, flour and 1/2 cup sugar in mixing bowl.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan and pour batter in. Next, pour peach mixture on top of batter.
Bake at 400° until top is brown.

title: spanish pork chops
directions: In large skillet, brown pork chops in margarine.
Add remaining ingredients in order listed.
Cover and simmer 1 hour or until rice is done.
Add water if necessary to keep from sticking.

title: confetti scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter; saute onions until tender.
Stir in all ingredients and half of cracker crumbs.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Add rest of cracker crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with Twinkies that have been sliced lengthways. Slice bananas and layer on top of Twinkies. Spread pineapple with juice on top of bananas. Mix pudding according to directions and place on top of pineapple. Spread Cool Whip on top of pudding. Sprinkle coconut and nuts on top.

title: marshmallow dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add salt, lemon and sugar.
Chill until syrupy.
Beat chilled milk until stiff. Whip gelatin and fold into cream.
Fold in marshmallows and pineapple.
Line pan with crumbs and top with crumbs.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well.
Add milk and flour.
Blend well.
Add coconut.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: 25 pounds beef barbecue
directions: Brown and drain ground beef and onions.
Simmer all ingredients in a large crab pot for 2 hours or divide into 2 large soup pots.
Serves approximately 100 to 125 people.

title: pistachio delight
directions: Mix together and press into 9 x 13-inch baking pan the crackers and melted butter.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: millionaires
directions: Melt paraffin in double boiler.
Add pecans.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Let harden for an hour.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together cream cheese, butter and water.
Add cake mix, oil, sugar and eggs.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: tropical float
directions: Combine ingredients and place in 2 refrigerator trays or a shallow pan.
Freeze almost solid.
Remove to bowl and beat until fluffy.
Return to freezer for several hours.

title: jo jo potatoes
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes.
Melt margarine in shallow baking pan.
Combine dry ingredients in bag.
Moisten potatoes with water.
Shake potatoes in bag with dry ingredients.
Place in single layer in margarine in pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender, turning once.
Serves 3 to 4.
French fries kids will love!

title: "philly" cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese and Cheddar cheese, mixing until blended. Add ham and onion.
Mix well.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in nuts and chill.
Serve with assorted crackers.
Yields 3 1/2 cups.

title: fruit cocktail pie
directions: Drain fruit.
Mix milk and lemon juice together.
Add rest and chill.

title: coconut gumdrop cookies
directions: Cream the butter.
Add sugar; beat well.
Stir in dry ingredients (which have been mixed together) alternately with beaten eggs.
Add coconut and gumdrops (cut into small pieces), then add rolled oats and vanilla.
Mix well.
Shape into small balls; press with fork.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Use a large skillet on top of stove and melt oleo.
Saute onion and celery in oleo.
Add salt, pepper, parsley and tuna. Brown lightly.
Stir in soup and water.
Cook noodles separately. Drain and rinse.
Add noodles to tuna mixture and simmer about 15 minutes or until desired consistency.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Layer whole graham crackers on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 3 cups milk and 2 packages pudding until thick.
Add Cool Whip. Put half of pudding over graham crackers.
Put on second layer of crackers.
Add rest of pudding.
Top with third layer of graham crackers, then frost with chocolate frosting.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: three fish mousse
directions: This dish is a marvelous first course, although a little goes a long way.
To begin, lightly oil a 2-quart ring mold.
Next, place the cod, bay leaf, lemon and peppercorns in a deep frying pan.
Cover with water and poach for about 25 minutes, or until the fish flakes.
Remove fish from stock and allow to cool.
Flake the fish.
Liberally line the ring mold with the smoked salmon, making certain that every slice overlaps a little with the next and that plenty is left to hang over the outer and inner edges of the mold.
Put 4 tablespoons of water into a saucepan.
Sprinkle the gelatin into the water and let the water completely absorb the granules.

title: ziti
directions: Cook and drain pasta.

Brown beef in skillet. Remove from heat and stir in cottage cheese, 1/2 of the Mozzarella and 1/2 of the Parmesan cheese. Add pasta and mix well. Pour 1/2 of the marinara in lightly greased 13 x 9-inch dish.
Add pasta and meat mixture. Top with sauce and cheeses.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Roll cookie dough out in a pizza pan.
Cook as directed on package.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Spread on cool cookie dough.
Arrange fruit as you like.
You can use any type of fruit you wish.

title: apple surprise
directions: You will need 1 plastic bag, scissors and aluminum foil.

title: skillet chicken divan
directions: Cook and stir chicken in hot oil in large skillet until browned.
Add water, wine, broccoli and soup.
Bring to boil. Stir in rice; cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes. Fluff with fork.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: glorified macaroni
directions: Cook
macaroni
in
salted
water
with small amount of butter.
Drain.
Mix
all ingredients together.
Put in casserole. Crumble saltines over top.
Cut up stick of butter over top of saltines.
Bake at 350° until bubbles around edges and butter is melted, about 15 minutes.

title: baked beans(serves 40 people)
directions: Open
beans; pour in large roaster.
Mix other ingredients with the
beans.
Cook
in	300° oven for 1 hour.
Do not cover the
roaster.
Stir beans every 15 minutes.
This serves 40 people, very good servings on take out plates.

title: five-spice walnuts
directions: Whisk egg whites in bowl until foamy.
Add grape juice, sugar and salt; mix well.
Stir in spices and walnuts and spread into two 10 x 15-inch baking pans, sprayed with nonstick spray.
Bake 1 hour at 250° or until walnuts are dry; stir occasionally.

title: cheese cake
directions: In a bowl, combine crumbs, margarine and 1/4 cup sugar.
Press on bottom and 1 1/2-inches up the sides of 8 or 9-inch spring-form pan.
In a bowl, with electric mixer at high speed, beat cream cheese, remaining sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Blend in sour cream and spread in prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes or until center is set.
Turn off oven.
Leaving door ajar, leave it in oven one hour.
Remove from oven and cool completely.
Chill four hours or overnight.
Remove sides of pan and top with pie filling.

title: party punch
directions: Add boiling water to jello and sugar; stir well until dissolved. Add cold water and juices.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Color of punch can be changed by using different kinds of jello.

title: dirt cake
directions: One medium-size flower pot (about 8-inches in diameter) works well for this recipe, or use 2 small pots, about 6-inches in diameter.
You will also need a garden trowel.

title: chicken and rice bake
directions: Line a 9 x 13 baking dish with uncooked bacon. Pour rice over bacon.
Mix 1 can cream of celery soup and 1 cup milk; pour over rice.
Top with uncooked boneless chicken breasts; season with Mrs. Dash or salt and pepper.
Combine 1 can cream of celery soup and 1 cup milk; pour over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Uncover and allow to bake for another 10 to 15 minutes. Serve with a salad and rolls.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: brownie cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Blend cake mix, coconut, butter and 1 egg on low speed until mixture is crumbly.
Press very lightly in ungreased baking pan (13 x 8 x 2-inch).

title: kit-kat bars
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with 1 layer of crackers.
Bring margarine, sugars, graham cracker crumbs and milk to a boil on medium heat.
Boil 5 minutes.
Pour 1/2 sauce over the layer of crackers.
Place another layer of crackers over sauce.
Pour remaining sauce over crackers.
Place another layer of crackers over sauce.
Melt chips and peanut butter and pour on top. Refrigerate until chocolate hardens.
Makes 30 servings.

title: hartwell's special
directions: Mix margarine, chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Melt all of this in the microwave until it gets real soupy.
When it gets thin, stir well and pour over Chex, nuts and pecans.
You will need a large bowl to mix well.
Put powdered sugar in a big bag, drop mixture and coat each piece.
Spread it on wax paper.
If it gets lumps, separate it.

title: almond joy cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on package.
Add pudding mix.
Bake in 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans (makes thin layers).
When done, set one aside.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Combine sour cream and mayonnaise; set aside.
Place shredded lettuce in bottom of large bowl or 9 x 13-inch dish.
Layer vegetables in given order.
Spread sour cream mixture over vegetables.
Sprinkle chopped eggs and bacon over sour cream.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, add egg and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together, add dry ingredients and milk to mixture. Add 1/2 cup extra flour to the candied fruits, nuts, raisins and coconut.
Mix until fruit is well coated.
Pour the batter over the fruits.
Add brandy flavoring and mix well.
Drop 1 teaspoon of mixture on a cookie sheet for each cookie.
Bake at 300° for 12 minutes or until the cookies are a light golden brown.
For decoration, put 1/2 candied cherry on top of each cookie before baking.

title: rum balls
directions: Place all ingredients in bowl.
Mix well.
Form small balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Keep in airtight container.
If moist, add more powdered sugar.
Please don't let the children at these. If you overeat, don't drive.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil in a large pot; set aside. Brown ground beef and drain excess fat.
Add ground beef, tomato products and spices to sauteed mixture.
Cook on low for 2 to 3 hours.

title: pineapple ice
directions: Combine and be sure all sugar is dissolved.
(Easy to do in crushed pineapple while squeezing juices).
Freeze in ice cube trays.
Serve topped with red cherry or 1 tablespoon ginger ale.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground meat and sausage separately in skillets.
Drain fat.
In a Dutch oven, place 1 tablespoon oil and saute onion and garlic.
Add meat, spaghetti sauce, tomatoes, oregano and seasonings to taste.
Simmer for about 20 to 25 minutes.
Cook noodles per instructions, using 1 tablespoon oil and salt to taste.

title: sweet 'n sour chicken
directions: Lightly saute pepper and onions.
Add hot water, carrots and bouillon.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
In separate bowl, combine sugar, cornstarch, ginger, catsup, vinegar and soy sauce.
Add to vegetables.
If using small pieces of uncooked chicken, saute with peppers and onions.
If using cooked chicken, add with condiments. Add pineapple, drained or with juice.
Stir and simmer 5 more minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: sweet rolls
directions: Rinse your bowl with hot water before putting warm water and yeast in it.
In another bowl mix hot milk, water, 2 tablespoons butter, 2 tablespoons sugar and salt.
When it is lukewarm, add to dissolved yeast mix.
Stir thoroughly.
Add 3 cups flour and stir. Add 2 1/2 to 3 cups more flour and knead on floured board for a few minutes.
Let rise in covered bowl until doubles in bulk.
Remove dough to floured surface.
Divide into 4 parts.

title: cherry kool-aid punch(good for dieters)
directions: Mix and freeze an ice tray full of mixture.
Add these ice cubes to the punch right before serving.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook sliced potatoes until tender (add chopped onion when cooking).
Drain.
Add all ingredients.
Put in microwave oven for 2 minutes before serving.
This serves 4 adults.
You could cook 12 potatoes and have some leftover for 1 or 2 nights.
Heats well in microwave.

title: school rolls
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Warm milk to 110°.
Pour milk into the bowl over the dry ingredients.
Add oil.
Mix with mixer for 5 minutes.
Place on a floured cutting board and roll out to 1/4 inch thick.
Cut out like biscuits.
Fold and place on a greased cookie sheet.
Spread melted butter on the top.
Let rise for 45 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 12 minutes or until brown.

title: nut roll-ups
directions: Mix margarine and cream cheese. Stir in flour until soft dough forms. Cover and refrigerate until firm, at least 8 hours.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; chill until thick. Add pineapple and pie filling; put in flat dish.

title: swedish pineapple cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in oiled pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch).
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool cake before frosting.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar together. Boil in saucepan the butter, cocoa and water. Remove from heat and pour over flour. Beat and mix well. Add buttermilk, eggs, soda, cinnamon and vanilla. Bake in ungreased 10 x 15 pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, until center springs back when touched.

title: cherry delight
directions: Melt marshmallows in 1 cup scalded milk.
Set aside to cool. Crush 2 packages (the individually wax wrapped ones) of graham crackers and mix with melted butter.
Put 1/2 of crumbs into 9 x 13-inch pan as the crust.

title: pudding delight
directions: Mix butter, flour and pecans; press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Mix and spread on cooled crust.
Make vanilla and chocolate pudding as directed and spread for next 2 layers.
Follow with a layer of Cool Whip and top with crushed pecans.

title: barbecued pork steaks
directions: Pound steaks with meat mallet.
For sauce, in a small bowl, combine the remaining ingredients; mix well.
Place steaks on grill about 4 inches above medium-slow coals.
Cook about 8 minutes on each side.
Brush steaks with sauce and continue cooking 5 minutes more, turning and brushing with sauce.

title: pot roast with zucchini sauce
directions: In a large heavy pot, over medium-high heat, brown beef and cook garlic in margarine.
Stir in 1 cup beef broth, tomato paste and Italian seasoning.
Heat to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 2 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Add zucchini. Cover and cook 10 minutes.
During the last 15 minutes of cooking time, cook macaroni in remaining broth according to package directions, omitting salt; drain. Serve zucchini sauce over sliced meat and macaroni.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: wassail
directions: Heat all of the ingredients.
Punch holes in orange and insert cloves.
Slice orange.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender; add salt.
Cut into cubes. Boil broccoli; drain and place in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Top with cubed chicken.
Combine sour cream and soup and mix together. Spread over chicken.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot through and through.

title: frankie's butterscotch dessert
directions: Press flour, oleo and 1/2 cup pecans in baking dish; bake in oven about 15 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Spread on first layer.
Next, mix instant pudding.
Spread on second layer.
Spread on rest of Cool Whip and top with remaining pecans.
Chill for about 2 hours before serving.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Layer Doritos, diced chicken and cheese alternately in greased baking dish.
Save enough cheese to cover top of casserole. Combine soup and tomatoes.
Spoon over layered ingredients and top with cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: low fat lasagne
directions: Brown turkey and onion in a large nonstick pan.
Drain off any fat.
Cook lasagne noodles as directed on package.
Add mushrooms and spaghetti sauce.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: crustless custard
directions: Beat the eggs and sugar until fluffy. Add the flour, milk and rest of ingredients.
Pour in greased pie pan.
Makes its own crust when baking.

title: poor man's pizza
directions: Clean thoroughly, 12 whole months.

title: french silk pie
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler and let cool.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy and smooth.
Blend in chocolate and vanilla.
Beat in eggs, taking approximately 5 minutes for each egg.
Pour into 9-inch precooked pastry shell and chill.

title: overnight chicken
directions: Mix together all but crumbs and put in 9 x 15-inch dish. Refrigerate overnight.
Set out 1 hour before baking and put bread or potato chip crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dream lime puff
directions: Mix gelatin, sugar and water. Refrigerate until thick. Add Cool Whip to remaining ingredients. Pour in a 8x13 inch casserole dish. Chill at least 4 hours or overnight. Cut in squares, serve over lettuce, if desired.

title: pear lime salad
directions: Drain pear juice from can of pears.
Add water to make 2 cups liquid.
Heat to boiling and pour over lime Jell-O and cream cheese.
Stir to dissolve.
Cool until firm.
Mix and blend crushed pears, Cool Whip and Jell-O mixture.
Can use electric mixer.
Chill until firm.

title: fried apples
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add apples and toss to coat. Add water.
Cover skillet and cook 8 to 10 minutes until tender, but firm.
Uncover; sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes longer.

title: teriyaki beef
directions: Mix together all ingredients except cornstarch.

title: party sandwich loaf
directions: Slice bread from end to end.
Grind the ham and cheese together; mix in the mayonnaise. Spread on the bread and stack in layers until all slices are back on the loaf.
To serve, cut across the sandwich.

title: peach cobbler
directions: *If using canned, sweetened peaches, omit adding sugar to peaches.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Toss in bowl the broccoli, onion, bacon and Mozzarella cheese. In a separate bowl, mix Miracle Whip salad dressing, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over salad and serve or can be refrigerated overnight.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
In a medium bowl, combine buttermilk, butter, egg and raisins.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, combine dry ingredients; with 2 forks, toss together for about 1 minute.
Combine all ingredients and mix until combined.
Spoon into prepared pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes; leave in pan for 1 minute and remove to wire rack to cool.

title: heavenly pie
directions: Put Eagle Brand in bowl with juice of 2 lemons.
Stir until thickened.
Drain pineapple.
Add pineapple and all other ingredients in the Eagle Brand mix.
Pour into pie crust after stirring all ingredients together real good.
Makes 2 pies.

title: "easy lasagna"
directions: In large skillet, brown and drain beef.
Add tomatoes and break up with fork.
Stir in tomato paste, garlic salt, oregano, basil leaves and mushrooms.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes or until thick.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes, peel and mash up.
Add oleo, egg, milk, vanilla and salt.
Cream well then add your Equal.
Do not overbake.
Bake at 350° for an hour.

title: mary's sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar and butter.
Add flavorings and mix thoroughly. Stir in dry ingredients together and blend.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours (the longer, the better). Roll dough to 1/6-inch.
Cut on lightly floured pastry cloth.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 2 to 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: barbecued possum
directions: Turn possum on its back and spread body cavity open.
Use a hatchet to split backbone down the middle so possum will spread flat on the grill.
Cook possum over medium coals, brushing often with mixture of melted margarine, vinegar and Dale's.
Just before possum is done throughout, brush inside and out with barbecue sauce and cook until barbecue sauce cooks into the meat.
Do not burn.

title: snowy fruit salad
directions: Cut fruit into bite size pieces.
Add raisins and pecans.
Mix sugar with sour cream (mix well); mix with fruit and nuts.
Top with drained cherries and coconut.

title: spicy oatmeal cake
directions: Add boiling water to oats in small bowl and let stand 5 minutes.
Blend sugars, oil and eggs.
Stir in oatmeal.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to mixture and beat well.
Stir in nuts. Spread in greased and floured pan, 9 x 13 x 2-inch.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes, or until toothpick test shows done.
Spread immediately with Broiled Frosting and broil for 3 to 5 minutes until brown.

title: banana split brownie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix brownie mix as directed on package. Place parchment paper on 15-inch baking stone.
Pour brownie mixture on paper and spread into 14-inch circle. Do not try without parchment paper; batter will run off stone while baking. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until set.
Cool.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix the ingredients and bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: strawberry pretzel mold
directions: Cream margarine with 3 tablespoons sugar.
Mix in pretzels. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°.
Cool. Cream the cream cheese and 1/4 cup sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip. Spread over crust.
Refrigerate 40 minutes.
Dissolve Jell-O in water; stir in strawberries.
Pour over cream cheese layer. Refrigerate overnight or until firm.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Roll out pizza dough on a floured table until size of a large pizza.
Cover dough with pepperoni and then Mozzarella.
Sprinkle with the chopped parsley.
Now slowly begin rolling pizza dough from one end to the other, making sure nothing is out on sides. When finished rolling place on ungreased cookie sheet with seam on bottom and ends tucked under.
Make 2 to 3 small holes on top for vapor.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 30 minutes until golden.
Enjoy!

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut top off peppers.
Remove seeds and rinse with water. Soak white bread in hot water for 1 minute.
Squeeze out excess water and add bouillon cube into bread to dissolve.
Mix bread into meat.
Add onion, nutmeg, pepper and eggs.
Mix well and stuff peppers.
In large saucepan heat oil and add peppers.
Fry for two minutes.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, basil and gravy mix.
Cook for 30 minutes over medium heat.
Serve with Rice.

title: peanut butter cream pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, until fluffy. Add sugar and peanut butter; mix well. Gradually add the milk, fold in whipped topping; spoon into the crust. Sprinkle with peanuts. Chill over night.

title: dill pickles
directions: Bring water, pickling salt and white vinegar to a boil.
Wash cucumbers in cool water.
Pack loosely in jars.
Place dill and corn or grape leaf in jar before you add the cucumbers.
Add garlic and powdered or chunky alum, pour liquid mixture over cucumbers and seal.

title: apple salad sauce
directions: Beat egg in saucepan.
Add sugar, flour, vinegar, salt and juice.
Bring to boil for 1 minute, stirring with a whip.
Remove from heat and cool.
Whip canned milk into mixture after cooled. Pour over apples and other ingredients to suit your own taste.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift together the flour, cinnamon, baking soda, sugar and salt.
Make a "well" in center of dry ingredients and add strawberries, eggs, oil and pecans.
Stir until moistened.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chile colorado
directions: Mix enchilada sauce and soup together.
Pour over meat and cook in crock-pot until meat is tender.

title: french dressing
directions: Combine and mix well.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk until thick.
Add sour cream. Fold in Cool Whip, lemon juice and flavoring.
In serving dish, layer wafers, banana slices and pudding mixture.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: In a large pot add onion, carrots, and potatoes. Cover with water and cook until almost done. While this is cooking, brown ground chuck until pink is gone. Drain and rinse with warm water. Add remaining ingredient to pot and season with salt and black pepper. Add water if needed for right consistency. Simmer for 30 - 45 minutes.

title: frosty cranberry mold
directions: Drain pineapple and cranberry sauce.
Save liquid and add enough water to make 2 cups.
Bring to a boil.
Dissolve jello in it and let set slightly.
Beat softened cream cheese and mayonnaise until fluffy.
Gradually add jello mixture.
Fold into whipped cream.
Add fruit, nuts and apples and pour into mold.

title: verboart apple pie filling(filling for 8 pies)
directions: Heat to boiling - water, cinnamon, sugar, salt, and lemon juice.
Thicken with corn starch mixed with 2 c. water.
Pour over 8 qt. of apples.
Place in quart jars and process for 20 minutes. You can also slice apples directly into qt jars and pour the mixture over them to fill jars.
Then process.
Filling for 8 pies.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Break eggs in bowl.
Beat with mixer.
Add sugar and beat. Add buttermilk and melted margarine.
Beat.
Then add coconut and vanilla.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Cool in refrigerator before rolling.
Roll thin; cut with cookie cutter.
Makes many, many cookies.

title: lookout mountain baked beans
directions: Cook beans 2 hours.
Add the rest of the ingredients; mix well.
Bake for 3 hours at 250°.
Makes 20 servings.

title: pierogi(filled dumplings)
directions: Mound flour on kneading board and make hole in center.
Drop eggs into hole and cut into flour with knife.
Add salt and water and knead until firm.
Let rest for 10 minutes, covered with a warm bowl.
Divide dough into halves and roll thin.
Cut circles with large biscuit cutter.
Place a small spoonful of filling a little to one side on each round of dough.
Moisten edge with water, fold over and press edges together firmly.
Be sure they are well sealed to prevent the filling from running out.
Drop pierogi into salted boiling water.
Cook gently for 3 to 5 minutes.
Lift out carefully with perforated spoon.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well.
Form into ball and chill.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix together all ingredients.

title: hot bean dip
directions: Fry and drain hamburger.
Add salsa sauce, refried beans, some onion and some Cheddar cheese.
Mix and place in square baking dish.
Top with more onion and more shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or microwave until hot and bubbly.
Serve with nacho type chips.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Soak beans overnight; drain.
In a large kettle, place beans and enough water to cover.
Add to beans, ham, parsley, onion, bay leaves, celery, pepper and garlic.
Simmer for 2 hours with lid removed.
Add the butter, Tabasco sauce and Worcestershire sauce. Cook an additional 2 hours, covered.
Serve hot over a bed of rice (preferably brown rice).

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring to boil water, cocoa and butter.
In a bowl mix flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.
In another bowl blend together vanilla, eggs and sour cream.
Add egg mixture to dry ingredients, blend with spoon, then add the boiled cocoa mixture.
Beat approximately 2 minutes with an electric mixer.
Bake at 350° in an 11 x 15 inch pan for 20 - 25 minutes.
While baking prepare icing.

title: salmon mousse
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water for 5 minutes.
Combine salt, mustard, cayenne pepper, egg yolks and milk in top of a double boiler.
Cook over hot (not boiling) water, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and coats back of spoon.
Remove from heat; add melted butter, lemon juice and gelatin.
Stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Fold in flaked salmon.
Turn into 1-quart mold which has been rinsed in cold water and chill until firm. Unmold on a bed of lettuce and serve with mayonnaise.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate peppermint dessert
directions: Line a 9 x 12 inch pan with crushed graham crackers, packed tightly. Reserve some crushed graham crackers for topping. Take 1/2 gallon softened peppermint ice cream and gently spoon it over graham cracker crust. Melt 1/2 of semi-sweet chocolate bar with butter. Gently pour the chocolate mixture over the softened ice cream. Sprinkle the top with crushed graham crackers. Freeze. Before serving, let it set out at room temperature for 1/2 hour. Cut into dessert squares. Makes 12 servings.

title: red chile stew
directions: Brown cubed beef in vegetable oil thoroughly; add red chili powder and flour.
Stir to a paste.
Gradually stir in the water. Add onions and garlic.
Simmer over low flame for 40 minutes. Stir in potatoes and cook 30 more minutes.
For thinner stew, add more water. Serves 6.

title: tolerine
directions: Saute onions and peppers in margarine; add meat and brown. Add tomato sauce, water, salt and pepper to taste.	Add uncooked noodles and stir until tender.
Add more liquid if necessary. Remove from heat and add corn.
Pour into a large casserole dish. Dot with butter.
Cover top with cheese.
Bake 40-45 minutes at 350°.

title: soft ginger cookies
directions: Combine flour, ginger, soda, cinnamon, cloves and salt.
Set aside.
In large mixing bowl, beat shortening to soften. Gradually add 1 cup sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add egg and molasses.
Beat well.
Stir dry ingredients into beaten mixture.

title: easy filled cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix thoroughly shortening, brown sugar and eggs.
Stir in water and vanilla.
Sift together and stir in flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Drop with teaspoon on ungreased baking sheet.
Place 1/2 teaspoon Date Filling on dough, cover with another 1/2 teaspoon of dough.
Bake until lightly brown, 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 5 to 6 dozen.

title: vegetable cream sauce
directions: Stir soup and milk in saucepan.
Simmer, whisking cheese until melted.
Add chives and garlic.
Season to taste.
Serve over broccoli, asparagus, cauliflower, potatoes or vegetable of your choice.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Toss with French or Mexican Spice dressing.

title: cheesy tuna burgers
directions: Combine tuna, mayonnaise, pickle, and onion; spread on hot dog buns.
Top each bun with 2 strips cheese.
Broil until bubbly.

title: cheese and spinach casserole
directions: Mix together flour and cheese.
Combine all ingredients until blended.
Put in greased casserole or 13 x 9-inch pan may be used. May be frozen and reheated.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour. Serves 10.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown beef, garlic, onion and green pepper.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and tomato paste; heat through.
Add basil, oregano, sugar and pepper.
Simmer about 15 minutes.
Serve over spaghetti noodles.
Serves about 4 to 6.

title: elva dexter's cranberry salad
directions: Drain syrup from fruit into 1-cup measure; add water to make one cup.
Heat to boiling in small saucepan.
Stir in gelatin and stir until gelatin dissolves.
Beat in cranberry sauce and add lemon juice.
Chill until thick as unbeaten egg white.
Stir in oranges, cottage cheese, celery and nuts.
Spoon into 6-cup mold. Chill several hours or overnight.

title: yummy yum yum bars
directions: Mix cake mix and water, pat into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.
Layer with marshmallows, M&M's and peanuts.
Bake 2 to 4 minutes or until melted.
Cool completely.
Cut into squares.
Serves 24.

title: new west chicken salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover and chill.
Makes 5 1/2 cups.
Serve on lettuce bed.

title: meat loaf roasted with cabbage
directions: Remove outer leaves of cabbage.
Cut in fourths and remove stalk.
Break leaves apart and cover bottom of roaster.
Sprinkle with salt; pour a little boiling water over.
Put on cover; set over fire to steam until a little wilted.
Mix and beat meat loaf mixture well.
Form 2 oblong loaves; place on top of cabbage. Place in oven; roast for about 2 hours.
Turn the loaves and stir cabbage occasionally.

title: angel pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add 1 cup sugar, a little at a time, beating after each addition.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla. Continue beating until mixture holds a soft peak.
Mix cracker crumbs and 1 cup pecans.
Fold into meringue a little at a time. Spoon mixture into an 8-inch pie plate with back of spoon; spread evenly.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool thoroughly on a wire rack.
Mix cream, 2 tablespoon sugar, 1 teaspoon vanilla and almond flavoring.
Whip until thick and shiny.
Spoon into cold pie shell.
Sprinkle remaining pecans around edge of cream.
Using a sharp knife, cut like a pie.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients. Prepare in ice cream freezer. Makes 3 gallons.

title: strawberry pan shortcake
directions: Tear angel food cake into bite size pieces and put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water, then add frozen strawberries.
Stir until berries are broken up.
Chill until barely soft set.
Pour Jell-O and strawberry mixture over angel food cake and top with Cool Whip.
Chill 2 hours or overnight.

title: honey soy chicken(microwave dish)
directions: Place chicken in 12 x 8-inch dish.
Combine honey, ginger, garlic and 1 tablespoon soy sauce.
Brush half of mixture over chicken.
Cook, covered with wax paper, on 100% power for 13 to 15 minutes, or until chicken juices run clear.
Brush with remaining half of mixture.

title: pork chops with stuffing
directions: Cook enough pork chops for each person.
Layer the stuffing (your favorite) and mushroom soup in a casserole dish and bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate meringue pie
directions: Prepare pastry crust according to recipe.
Combine cornstarch, sugar, salt and chocolate in a saucepan.
Stir in milk gradually. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Blend half the mixture into egg yolks.
Stir into mixture in saucepan; cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter or margarine and vanilla.
Cool slightly.
Pour into pastry shell and bake as directed in Basic Meringue Recipe.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant in small bite-size pieces; this will take about 2 months.
Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Simmer on kerosene fire for about 4 weeks.
Serve stew over steaming rice.
Yields approximately 3,800 servings.
If more are expected the 2 rabbits may be added.
This should only be done if absolutely necessary because most people do not like to find hare in their stew.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegar.
Break veggies into bite size pieces.
Add bacon.
Add cheese.
Pour mixture over veggies and stir.
Put in fridge overnight.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Peel and dice apples.
Sprinkle with lemon juice so they won't turn dark.
Add mayonnaise and mix. Then add the other ingredients. Chill in refrigerator for 1 hour before serving.

title: italian pot roast
directions: Put olive oil in skillet and preheat for approximately 3 minutes.
Add pot roast and brown both sides.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer on medium heat until meat is done, approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: oven-barbecued round steak
directions: Cut meat into 6 to 8 serving pieces.
Brown meat in oil for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Transfer meat to an ungreased casserole. Mix remaining ingredients; pour over meat.
Cover and cook in a 325° oven until tender, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Place all dry ingredients in bowl.
Blend in shortening with pastry blender or fork.
Add eggs and milk.
Add cut up gumdrops; drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: garlic bubble bread
directions: Combine butter, egg, parsley, salt and garlic.
Cut dough into walnut sized pieces.
Dip dough into butter mixture.
Place in well-greased loaf pan.
Cover.
Let rise until doubled in size. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool on rack. Butter top while still warm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: jennifer's chicken
directions: Fry bacon; remove from grease.
Crumble bacon and put into the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour margarine over bacon. Boil chicken and pull into small pieces.
Put over bacon and margarine.
Mix soups, sour cream and milk and pour over chicken. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until well heated.
Serve over cooked pasta.

title: blueberry baskets
directions: Place 1 ball of dough in each of 12 greased muffin cups.
Let stand at room temperature 1 hour or until thawed.
Combine sugar, flour and spices.
Make a deep indentation in middle of each ball of dough.
Fill indentation with 1 teaspoon brown sugar mixture and 1 rounded tablespoon blueberries.
Sprinkle evenly with remaining brown sugar mixture.
Top each with 1/2 teaspoon butter. Let dough rest 15 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until dough browns.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion together.
Season with salt, pepper and a pinch of sugar.
Add egg.
Put in casserole dish and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Pour mushroom soup over this.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Pour melted oleo over top.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: squash and potato scallop
directions: Melt margarine in a skillet.
Add potatoes, squash, onion and bell pepper.
Cook until desired doneness and season to taste. Pour mixture into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place shredded cheese on top.
Bake at 350° just until cheese melts.

title: sausage and ziti combo casserole(serves 8)
directions: In a large skillet, brown sausage until well done (remove casing first).
Drain off excess fat.
Add onions and sauce to sausage.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: cold sesame noodles
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let sit a couple of hours.
Once all the ingredients are stocked, they last a long time and it's a great way to use leftover chicken or make a "special" dinner for surprise guests.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.
Decorate top with pecan halves and cherries.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat with onion in a large pot, then add tomatoes, beans and sauce.
In a small bowl, mix together salt, pepper, bay leaves, chili powder, oregano, cumin, whole allspice, sugar, cinnamon and garlic powder.
Add spices to meat mixture.
Set on medium and cook for 20 minutes.

title: chicken livers
directions: Roll livers in flour and brown with onions.
On the side, boil water and add bouillon cube.
Pour over livers, add wine and seasonings.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: hawaiian ham
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix brown sugar, cornstarch and pineapple juice.
Pour over ham and pineapple.
Cook in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Heat until hot through or sauce has thickened.
If sauce is too thick, add more juice.

title: jefferson davis pie
directions: In large bowl, blend sugar, flour and nutmeg.
Stir in cream; add eggs.
Mix well.
Add lemon juice, lemon peel and butter. Beat well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 45 minutes or until center is almost firm.
It is very rich.

title: baked cabbage and butter cantonese
directions: Cut pork loin into paper-thin bite-size pieces; rinse cabbage lightly; drain and cut into bite-size pieces.
Precook cabbage pieces in boiling water until soft (add stalk pieces of cabbage first); remove and drain.
Heat pan and 4 tablespoons oil; stir-fry pork loin until it changes color.
Add cabbage and stir-fry briefly over high heat; add m.s.g., salt, sugar and water.
Turn heat to medium and cook 10 minutes; remove and drain off liquid to a bowl (retain).
Place cabbage in a casserole.
Heat pan and butter; saute onion until soft; add flour and stir-fry over low heat until fragrant.
Add retained cabbage soup and evaporated milk; mix. Pour over cabbage, preheat oven to 350° and bake cabbage casserole for 20 minutes.
Remove and serve.

title: beet salad
directions: Drain beets, reserving liquid; add water to reserved liquid to equal 2 cups in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat; stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Add cold water, onion, horseradish, vinegar and salt.
Chill until partially set.
Stir in the beets, celery and olives.
Pour into an 8-inch square dish or mold.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Cut into squares, if desired, and serve on lettuce-lined plate.
Top with a dollop of mayonnaise and an olive (or unmold on glass plate and garnish). Yield:
9 to 12 servings.

title: carrot salad
directions: Combine carrots, raisins and celery.
Mix sour cream with remaining ingredients; blend into salad.
Chill.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: yummy mud
directions: Mix pudding as directed.
Put in worms.
Top with rock candy.

title: beat and eat frosting
directions: Put sugar, cream of tartar, vanilla, boiling water and egg white in a bowl.
Beat on high.

title: creamy cucumbers
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; fold in cucumber.
Sprinkle with paprika and allow to chill.

title: cabbage and chicken
directions: In a paper or plastic bag, mix flour, seasoned salt and celery seed.
Add chicken legs, a few at a time; shake to coat.

title: navaho fry bread
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder into a bowl.
Stir in water and milk.
Knead with hands.
Pat or roll into circles, approximately 5-inches in diameter.
With fingers make small hole in center.
Fry in several inches hot oil at 400°.
Electric skillet is convenient.
Dough will puff and bubble.
Turn when golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Serve hot with honey or make Navajo tacos.

title: rhubarb meringue pie
directions: Place rhubarb in pie shell.
Combine beaten egg yolks, sour cream, flour and 1 cup sugar.
Mix well and pour over rhubarb. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 325°.
Bake 30 minutes or until center is firm.
Beat egg whites until stiff; gradually beat in 2 tablespoons sugar.
Top pie with meringue; bake until brown.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: brownies
directions: Mix and bake at 375° for 25 minutes, no longer.

title: red-cooked pork shoulder
directions: Soak mushrooms 30 minutes in warm water.
Leave whole.
Blanch pork and let boil briskly for 5 minutes.
Transfer meat to colander. Run hot tap water over it. Discard cooking water. Replace the meat in the pot.
Add soy sauce, star anise, rock candy, wine, scallions and 2 cups cold water. Bring to a boil and cover the pot.
Reduce heat to low. Cook about 3 hours, adjusting heat to keep the liquid at simmer, turning meat over 2 or 3 times during the cooking period.
Add soaked mushrooms.
Cook 30 minutes longer.
There should be about 1 cup liquid left.
If more, cook, uncovered, until liquid is reduced. Transfer to deep platter. Pour cooking juice over it.
Serves 6 to 8 main course or 8 to 10 as part of a Chinese meal.

title: toasted praline sauce
directions: Combine egg yolks, sugar and butter in heavy saucepan over low heat.
Stir until well blended.
Add cream, bourbon and vanilla. Bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 5 to 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, stir in pecans. Refrigerate until ready to use.
Reheat and serve over pound cake. Contains 78 calories per serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all
ingredients and place in large casserole dish. Cover with
cup
crushed
corn
flakes mixed with 1/8 cup butter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon garlic chicken
directions: Place butter in square baking dish.
Melt in microwave.
Add lemon juice and garlic.
Place chicken in mixture.
Cover with mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Cover pan with aluminum foil.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: too good to name cake
directions: Bake yellow cake as directed in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.
Drain pineapple and spread over cake.
Make vanilla pudding as directed and mix in cream cheese.
Layer this on top of pineapple.
Next layer bananas, then Cool Whip.
Sprinkle pecans over cake and decorate with cherries cut in half.

title: baked beans
directions: Microwave onion and bacon on High for 1 minute.
Add onion and bacon to beans.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer on stove for 20 minutes or microwave on High for 15 minutes.
Or may be cooked in a crock-pot on low setting for 4 or 5 minutes.
Delicious!

title: easy apple pie
directions: Mix well.
Place in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: key lime pie
directions: Blend softened cream cheese with condensed milk, using mixer at low speed. Add limeade and continue mixing. Fold in (do not use mixer) the container of Cool Whip. Pour into graham cracker pie crust. Put in freezer for 2 hours or until set. Serve and enjoy!

title: stuffed chicken
directions: Debone chicken for stuffing.
Marinate chicken in a bowl in soy sauce and lemon juice overnight.
Blend in bowl the ground pork, chicken, sausage, cheese, relish, raw eggs, salt, pepper, Accent and melted margarine (butter).
Stuff chicken with mixture, arranging sliced eggs in the center of the mixture without overstuffing chicken.
Sew opening and wrap tightly in aluminum foil.

title: date and nut bars
directions: Beat egg; add sugar.
Add vanilla.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Stir in dates and nuts.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
When cool, cut into squares.
Shake 1 or 2 at a time in a bag with small amount of confectioners sugar.
Keep tightly covered. (Contains no shortening.)

title: cold crab dip
directions: Mix together first 8 ingredients.
Add cream cheese and crabmeat.
Serve on crackers.

title: special peach pie
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Beat eggs with sugar and add to peach mixture.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 350° until set, about 25 minutes.

title: my kids like it spinach soup
directions: Cook onion and garlic in microwave or steamer until soft.
Add water and bouillon.
Bring to a boil; stir and add noodles and salt.
Cook uncovered 10 minutes.
Then add the spinach.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in milk, cheeses and pepper.
Stir until melted but do not boil.

title: delicious rolls
directions: Combine 2 cups water, butter, salt and sugar in a large pot. Warm until butter, salt and sugar dissolve.
Let cool in pot until warm to touch and not hot.
Prepare to add yeast.
Combine 1/4 cup warm water with sugar and yeast packet until yeast is dissolved. Add mixture to large pot.
Stir in flour.
Grease baking pans.
Use about 2 tablespoons dough for each roll.
Fills 2 (9 x 13-inch) glass pans.
Let rise until dough has doubled in size or between 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes or until rolls are browned.
Eat with butter and enjoy.
Makes 48 rolls.

title: spinach appetizer
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand several hours or overnight. Right before serving, spoon into sourdough round loaf of bread that center has been cut out of.
Cube bread from center of loaf and use this to dip into spinach mixture.

title: ro's killer beans
directions: Cook bacon with onions.
Add beef and brown.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Put in 2-quart greased baking dish. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: lentil chicken salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first 6 ingredients. In a small bowl, combine the mayonnaise, salsa, onions and lemon juice. Pour over salad and stir gently to coat. Serve immediately.

title: lazy day lasagna(microwave recipe)
directions: Crumble beef in casserole dish.
Microwave on High power for 4 minutes, stirring once and drain.
Stir in the tomatoes and juice, tomato paste, salt, basil, oregano and garlic powder.
Cover with lid and microwave on High power 4 to 6 minutes.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Blend egg yolks, cornstarch, salt, sugar, lemon rind and juice.
Add
to
boiling water, stir over low heat until thick. Add butter.
Pour
into
a	baked
pie crust; top with meringue made with egg whites.
Return to oven to brown.

title: three little baker's decorating icing
directions: Cream the shortening. Blend in milk and vanilla. Sift sugar and salt together. Slowly add to mixture. Whip to a light consistency.

title: whip cream cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add
eggs, one at a time. Beat after each addition.
Add
flour and whipped cream gradually. Add flavoring and
beat
until
creamy.
Pour
into
a 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fluffy peach cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray three 8-inch round cake pans with nonstick cooking spray.
Prepare cake mix as directed, following no cholesterol recipe.
Spoon batter evenly into pans.
Bake 25 minutes until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool cake in pans for ten minutes.
Drain peach juice into large bowl.
Chop peach slices.
Add whipped topping, pudding mix and chopped peaches, stirring gently to combine.
Refrigerate peach mixture, covered, until ready to assemble cake.
When cake is cool, place 1 layer on plate.
Spread 1/4 cup peach mixture.
Top with second layer.
Spread 1/4 cup mixture.
Top with third layer.
Frost top and sides of cake with remaining mixture.
Refrigerate cake until ready to serve.
Makes 16 servings.
Each serving:
about 125 calories and 4 grams fat.

title: baked chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix together chicken, celery, onion, green pepper, salt, mushrooms, mayonnaise, lemon juice and chicken soup.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with grated cheese and potato chips. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pickled vidalia onions (or pickled yellow squash)
directions: Put onions, bell peppers and salt in ice water for 1 hour. Mix vinegar, sugar, celery seed and mustard seed.
Bring to a boil.
Add onion mix to vinegar mix and bring to a second boil. Place in boiled jars and seal.
Makes about 4 pints.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat after each.
Add gradually the butter, milk, lemon juice and lemon rind.
Bake in unbaked shell at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: salsa chicken
directions: Combine flour and taco mix in a small bowl.
Beat eggs with water in another bowl.
Dip each chicken piece in flour mix.
Coat with egg, then roll in cornmeal.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Melt butter with oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and fry until done (about 3 minutes per side).
Transfer to baking pan.
Top each chicken piece with 2 slices of cheese and 2 tablespoons salsa.
Broil until cheese melts.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: In a jelly roll pan, lay out 2 packs of Pillsbury crescent rolls.
Pinch together seams and bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and Hidden Valley Ranch dressing mix. Spread mixture on crescents and top with finely chopped broccoli, carrots, Cheddar cheese, onion and red pepper.
Cut and serve.

title: sourdough bread starter
directions: Mix well; feed starter every 5 to 7 days.
Cover lightly with paper towel; let stand out of refrigerator 8 to 12 hours.
Take 1 cup out.
Make bread; give to a friend or toss 1 cup out.

title: london broil
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Cook onions.
Add 1/4 teaspoon salt in butter; cook until tender.
Keep onions warm over heat.
Stir together, salad oil, lemon juice, garlic, salt and pepper.
Brush on top side of meat.

title: texas pecan cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Gradually add flour, soda and fruit which has been dredged in part of flour. Add other ingredients.
Lightly fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in tube pan, lightly greased and lined with wax paper.
Use foil over and under pan.
Bake for 4 hours at 250°.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put bottom crust on 9-inch pie plate. Pour in all ingredients.
Fold top crust over plate and flute sides.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
If edges start to get too dark, put aluminum foil around.

title: 3 vegetable cheese bake
directions: Let vegetables thaw.
Place vegetables in 2-quart casserole. Slice chunks of Velveeta over vegetables.
Spoon soup over Velveeta.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until bubbly.
Stir once halfway through cooking.

title: easy banana cake
directions: Mix yellow cake mix per directions on box.
Add 2 large or 3 small mashed bananas, 1/2 cup ground walnuts, 1 teaspoon baking powder and 1 tablespoon vinegar to batter.
Beat together.
Bake as directed on box.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together milk, Jiffy cornbread mix and egg.
Add 2 different styles of corn, oleo, onions and 1/2 cup cheese.
Add green peppers, if wanted.
(Use 13 x 9-inch pan.)

title: green pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Chill and serve on lettuce leaves with grated cheese sprinkled on top.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Mix together soft drink, cinnamon, sugar and nutmeg.
Simmer until sugar dissolves.
Add butter and remove from heat.
Peel, core and cut apples in half.
Roll out pastry and cut into squares large enough for each half apple.
Sprinkle apples with additional cinnamon, sugar and butter.
Fold pastry over apples and place in baking dish.
Pour syrup over the apples and pastry.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fiesta dip
directions: In a medium skillet prepare taco seasoning with ground beef and water according to package directions.
Add refried beans and heat for 5 minutes.
In a 1-quart bowl, spread beef and bean mixture.
Layer Cheddar cheese, olives, tomato, sour cream, salsa and onion (in this order).
Serve immediately.

title: sweet 'n sour pork or chicken
directions: Coat skillet with Pam and cook meat until brown.
Add water. (Cover and simmer pork only for 30 minutes.)
Drain pineapple and set aside.

title: texas pie topping
directions: Mix topping well and add to the top of the prepared crust and Texas Pie filling.
Add extra chopped peanuts to sprinkle on top.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together; put in a casserole dish (1 1/2 to 2-quart).
Bake in a slow oven (300°), stirring occasionally until milk is absorbed (approximately 1 1/4 hours).

title: parmesan crisps
directions: On cutting board, unfold one pastry sheet.
In small cup, beat egg with tablespoon of water.
Brush pastry with some egg mixture; sprinkle with 1/4 cup cheese and 1/8 teaspoon paprika.
With rolling pin, press lightly into pastry.
Turn over; repeat.

title: beef-a-roni(makes 100 servings)
directions: Brown meat with onions in steam kettle with 2 gallons water. Add vegetables and seasonings.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Add macaroni.
Bring to a boil.
Cook until done.

title: basic roll recipe
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water; add salt and sugar.
Add eggs and beat. Melt the shortening in 1/2 cup hot water; add 1/2 cup cool water. When cooled to warm, add to first mixture. Stir in the flour, about half at a time.
Knead until of the right consistency, adding only a sprinkle of flour as needed to avoid being too stiff. Cover and let rise in a warm place. Shape and let double in bulk.
Bake in hot oven (400°) until lightly browned. Brush with melted butter.

title: pap's venison roast
directions: Heat oven to 225° to 250°.
Place roast in the center of a large cast-iron pot.
Add potatoes, celery and carrots around roast.
Place sliced onion on top of roast.
Add salt, pepper, seasoned salt and hot sauce to taste.
Cover with glass lid and slowly bake for 3 1/2 to 4 hours (or until very tender).

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix and let blend in refrigerator for at least 24 hours.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Combine all in blender.
Serve with favorite chips or vegetables.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick butter and graham cracker crumbs.
Beat the powdered sugar, 2 sticks butter and eggs with an electric mixer 15 minutes.
Pour filling over crust.
Layer pineapple and bananas. Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle nuts and cracker crumbs over top.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Note:
Don't add salt all at once.
Taste, then add more, if needed.

title: pork roast
directions: Freeze pork sausage. Use a butcher knife and cut an X through the roast from end to end and stuff the frozen sausage through the roast. Rub the roast down with the sauce and seasonings. Cut slits in the roast and stuff pieces of green pepper. Bake at 325° for 2 hours in an open pan.

title: cocoa fudge(microwave)
directions: Microwave sugar, cocoa, milk and butter on High until butter is melted, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir until smooth.
Blend in vanilla and nuts.
Spread into a buttered 8-inch square pan. Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: chili rellano casserole
directions: Rinse chilies.
Remove veins and seeds.
Pat dry with paper towel.
Layer half of chilies and half of cheese in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Repeat, saving 1 cup cheese for topping.
Beat eggs.
Add flour and milk and beat until well blended.
Pour over chilies and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Then spread on tomato sauce with desired amount of salsa added.
Sprinkle on remaining cheese and bake 15 minutes more or until cheese melts and is lightly browned.

title: ham and egg brunch
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Place bread cubes and ham in bottom; top with cheese.
Combine eggs, milk and mustard. Pour over cheese layer.
Top with margarine.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 325°.
Easy and delicious!

title: butterscotch pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites and gradually beat in sugar to form meringue. Top with chopped pecans.
Cook in oven at 325° for 10 minutes or so.

title: potato-meat casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and place in greased casserole. Pour gravy over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: angel buns
directions: Mix yeast, sugar and baking mix in bowl; add water and milk until dough forms.
Gently smooth into ball on surface dusted with baking mix.
Knead 10 times.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter dipped in baking mix.
Place on ungreased sheet. Let rise in warm place about 30 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Makes 9 to 11 buns.

title: peg's never fail icing
directions: Mix flour and milk slowly; bring to boil.
Remove from heat. Cool.
Cream Crisco and sugar.
When flour and milk mixture is cool, combine both and beat until fluffy.
When nearly done, add vanilla and beat awhile longer.

title: cherry delight
directions: Melt oleo and mix with graham cracker crumbs.
Press in the bottom of 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix the cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread over crumb mixture.
Spread cherry pie filling over cream cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip; sprinkle chopped nuts on top of Cool Whip.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli, water and mushrooms until tender.
Melt margarine and flour in small saucepan, stirring, to make a roux; set aside.

title: beef barley soup
directions: In large bowl, dredge meat cubes in flour.
In 6-quart pot, brown meat and garlic in oil.
Drain fat, if necessary.
Add water, tomatoes, barley, Worcestershire sauce, salt, basil and pepper.
Bring to boil, cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil, cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 to 25 minutes, or until meat and vegetables are tender. Makes about 4 quarts.

title: watergate #1
directions: Pour pineapple juice over marshmallows.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Sprinkle pudding mix and nuts on top.
Add whipped topping and mix.
Set in refrigerator.

title: pork chops in tomato sauce
directions: Salt and pepper chops; brown in oil.
Pour off excess fat. Sprinkle lemon juice, sugar and seasonings over chops.
Pour tomato sauce over all.
Cover; simmer for 1 hour, or until tender. Serve, using sauce over rice or noodles.

title: cabbage
directions: Quarter cabbage in 6 parts.
Cut out heart.
Boil in salted water for 15 minutes; drain.
Place cabbage in buttered dish. Layer pepper, sugar, oleo and tomatoes.
Sprinkle top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Season chicken.
Put in pan or dish.
Add chicken soup to dish. Pour over chicken.
Add 1/2 to 1 can of water and stir. Cook 1 hour, stirring in between.
Then add onions, green peppers, celery and package of gravy mix.
(Note: Gravy mix can be added along with chicken soup.)
Continue to cook 1/2 hour to 1 hour until done.
Cook on 300° to 350°.

title: toasted crab muffins
directions: Beat cream cheese, milk, lemon juice and hot pepper seasoning together.
Mix in the onions and crab meat.
Split, butter and toast the muffins.
Spread cheese mixture over hot toasted side of muffin.
Broil just until top browns slightly.
Makes 6 to 8 open-faced sandwiches (6 is more generous).

title: chewy chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the butter, peanut butter and shortening with sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Blend into creamed mixture. Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes (do not overbake). Cookies will be soft; they will puff during baking and flatten upon cooling.
Cool on cookie sheet until set, about 1 minute. Makes about 4 1/2 dozen (depending on size of cookies).

title: put back potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes well; prick some holes in them with a fork.
Rub potatoes with a small amount of oil.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool.
Cut potatoes lengthwise and scoop out insides.
Put into a bowl.
Save the skins.
Save 1/3 cup of cheese for topping.
Mix the rest of the cheese, milk, salt and pepper with potatoes.
Add margarine.
Using a mixer or masher, mix all together while warm.

title: bread pudding for 2
directions: Beat egg, sugar, milk, salt and vanilla together lightly and pour over bread in buttered casserole.
Add either coconut, grated apple or raisins.
You can also use some cake crumbs or sweet rolls, etc.
Bake in slow oven at 300° until custard is set.

title: strawberry coffee cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and beat until light and fluffy. Stir in the milk, eggs and vanilla. Sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Add to cheese-egg mixture. Mix until smooth; batter will be stiff. Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan and spread 1/2 of the batter on the bottom. Spread fruit pie filling or preserves evenly over the batter. Dot remaining batter over the top and spread gently. Some filling will show through. Mix brown sugar and nuts. Sprinkle over cake. Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°. Drizzle warm cake with a powdered sugar glaze.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken until done. Steam or microwave broccoli until just starting to soften (still fairly firm). Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, curry and salt in bowl. In 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, layer the chicken and broccoli and spread the sauce evenly over the top. Cook 15 minutes at 350°.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Layer half of the vanilla ice cream on the bottom and sides of a chilled 8 x 3-inch round pan.
Next, layer the fudge sauce. Freeze.
In a mixing bowl, coat crushed chocolate wafers with chocolate syrup.
Use only enough syrup to coat.
Layer this mixture on top of wafer mixture to fill pan evenly.
Freeze overnight.

title: pineapple date nut cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs and beat.
Add liquid, mix and then add flour, salt and soda.
Mix well, then add pineapple, dates and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet and bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: round steak barbecue
directions: Cut meat into bite size pieces.
In large frypan, brown meat in oil.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Stir together.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Serve with your favorite side dish.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put in well-greased and floured loaf pans or in prepared 1-pound coffee cans filled only half full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until done.

title: moist 'n creamy coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package, baking in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool 15 minutes. Poke holes in cake with a utility fork.
Meanwhile, combine milk, sugar and 1/2 cup of coconut in saucepan.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 1 minute. Spoon evenly over warm cake.
Chill in refrigerator.
Fold 1/2 cup coconut into Cool Whip and spread over cake.
Sprinkle with remaining coconut.
Chill overnight. Keep refrigerated.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms; remove stems.
Sprinkle mushroom caps with lemon juice; brown stems in butter, then add to garlic, bread crumbs, cheese, onion and sausage.
Mix together.
Pile into mushroom caps.
Sprinkle with more bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chocolate caramel candy
directions: Combine chips and peanut butter in a small saucepan; stir over low heat until melted and smooth.
Spread onto the bottom of a lightly greased 13X9x2 pan.
Refrigerated until set.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Step 1:
Soak cucumbers 1 week (3 days will do) in a brine made of 1 pint pickling salt to 1 gallon water.

title: one pot pork chop supper
directions: In an electric skillet, brown chops.
Pour off fat.
Add cut up potatoes and cut up carrots.
Cover with the mixed together soup, water, salt, Worcestershire sauce and oregano.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes or until tender.

title: hearty potato soup
directions: In 3-quart pan, put carrots, celery, onion and then potatoes. Pour in broth and add enough water to cover vegetables.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add butter.
Boil until tender.
Add milk.
Cook 15 minutes more.
Enjoy!

title: caramel corn
directions: Pop
corn,
pick
out seeds and set aside.
Put butter, brown sugar,
Karo
syrup and salt into saucepan until butter melts. Bring
to

on medium heat.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and baking
soda; stir

pan;	mix well.
Bake
at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every

Cool
on wax paper and store in a tin.

title: crock-pot macaroni
directions: Place stick of butter in bottom of crock-pot.
Layer macaroni and cheese (save some cheese to sprinkle on top); stir as you add. Stir in milk and salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Mix egg and evaporated milk; pour over top of everything.
Do not stir!!! Cook on low for 3 1/2 hours.
Enjoy!!!

title: dutch oven dinner
directions: In hot oil in Dutch oven, cook beef, stirring for about 10 minutes.
Stir in salt and next five ingredients.
Top with uncooked noodles.
Sprinkle with 1 cup cheese; pour tomatoes over all.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with hot water, then add cold water.
Add crushed pineapple; grate orange rind and add it to the mixture along with the juice of the orange.
Add sugar and whole cranberry sauce. Chill until set.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In large pan mix first 4 ingredients and bring to a full boil and boil for 1 minute.
Take off burner then add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well with large spoon.
Then with a teaspoon, drop on waxed paper and you can put a little coconut in the center of the cookie or a cherry or piece of walnut for decoration while cookie is still hot.
Let cool for at least 2 hours.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Cook fryer and bone.
Add onion, celery, mayonnaise, almonds, chicken soup and broth.
Mix well and place in 13 x 9-inch pan. Cover with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: coconut dream pie
directions: Prepare Dream Whip with 1 cup milk and vanilla as directed on package.
Add remaining 1 3/4 cups milk to pudding mix.
Blend, then beat at high speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in coconut.
Spoon into pie shell.
Chill 4 hours.

title: cheese broccoli soup
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Mix broccoli chicken, onion and pepper in a sauce pan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce to low heat and cook until tender.
About 10 minutes.
Process in blender until smooth. Return to stove and add all but 1/4 cup of milk.
Bring to boil stirring occassionaly.
Add corn starch to the 1/4 cup milk and mix until smooth.
Add slowly to the boiling mixture.
Simmer on low for 10 more minutes.

title: new waldorf salad
directions: In a large bowl, toss together fruit.
In a small bowl, mix remaining ingredients (except lettuce) gently.
Cover and chill for 2 to 24 hours.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Contains 210 calories if using reduced calorie mayonnaise.

title: strawberry custard
directions: Beat egg until frothy in top of double boiler.
Combine sugar, flour and salt; gradually add to egg, beating until thick.
