Place milk and pureed strawberries in a saucepan; cook over low heat until thoroughly heated; do not boil.
Gradually stir about one-fourth of hot milk into egg mixture; add remaining milk, stirring constantly.
Bring water in double boiler to a boil. Reduce heat to low.
Cook 10 to 20 minutes or until mixture thickens and coats a metal spoon.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour custard into a bowl and chill.
To serve, place 1/2 cup strawberries in each of 4 stemmed glasses.
Drizzle 1/4 cup chilled custard over each serving.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes until golden brown and top is firm. Serves 8.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients together and cook in a 7-inch skillet if you have one.
Bake at 450° until browned.
You may substitute 1 package cornmeal mix.

title: tomato sauce for veal
directions: In hot oil in skillet, saute onion and garlic until golden brown.
Add salt and remaining ingredients, breaking up tomatoes with fork.
Bring to boil; simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.

title: marinated chuck roast
directions: Tenderize roast with unseasoned tenderizer.
Mix last seven ingredients together.
Cut chuck roast into 2 to 3-inch pieces. Pour marinade mixture over meat and marinate 2 to 3 hours.
Best grilled or broiled.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers and salt and refrigerate 1/2 hour.
Do not drain juice.
Then add onion, green pepper, celery seed, sugar and white vinegar.
Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and refrigerate.
Will keep a long time.

title: pavlova australia
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.
Gradually add sugar on lowest setting of mixer.
Add vanilla, malt vinegar and cornstarch.
Blend into egg whites.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Combine coconut and milk.
Stir in vanilla and chocolate chips.
Set oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Drop teaspoonfuls 1-inch apart on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes or until light brown.
Remove at once and cool.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: my mother's cheese pudding
directions: Layer bread and cheese in buttered casserole.
Beat balance of ingredients until fluffy and pour over cheese and bread.
Let stand in refrigerator (covered) overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until well set.
Serve immediately.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into greased 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.
tags: cream of chicken and mushroom soup

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Use pastry blender to combine these ingredients.
Sprinkle over top of pie.
Return to oven for 35 to 45 minutes until filling is set.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, molasses and eggs.
Add hot water and dry ingredients.
Roll to 1/4-inch thickness.
Sprinkle with sugar and bake in hot oven.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs well and mix the rest of the ingredients together. Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes. Makes 2 pies.

title: coffee punch for 35
directions: Dissolve coffee and sugar in hot water.
Cool.
Add the milk. Chill overnight.
Just before serving, add the ice milk.
Put in punch bowl.
Chop in chunks.

title: meatballs or meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients. Add water if too dry. More bread crumbs if too moist. Shape into meatballs or loaf. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes for meatballs or 1 to 1 1/4 hours for meat loaf.

title: curried rice-bean salad
directions: Combine first six ingredients.
Toss to mix.
In separate bowl, combine mayonnaise, yogurt, curry powder and black pepper. Blend thoroughly with rice/bean mixture.
Yield: 6 servings. Approximate calories/serving:

title: halloween punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and when ready to serve, add 1 quart of ginger ale and decorate with orange slices.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat egg whites stiff. Gradually add vanilla, vinegar and sugar and continue beating until stiff peaks form. Fold in pecans and chocolate or butterscotch morsels. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto foil-covered cookie sheet. Place in the oven and TURN OFF THE HEAT. Leave at least 5 hours or overnight.

title: stuffed tomato surprise
directions: Cook bacon until crisp;
drain, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings.
Crumble bacon and set aside.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix thoroughly and let sit in refrigerator overnight (if possible).
Form 1-inch balls and bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 50+ balls.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, eggs and peanut butter.
Add flour and soda; mix well.
Roll into balls.
Place on cookie sheet and press down with fork tines which have been dipped in flour.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: baked chicken dinner
directions: Slice the butter over the top (1/4 cup of butter).
Place raw vegetables in a roaster with a tight fitting top.
Place chicken halves on top of vegetables.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and half and half cream over the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: paul's onions
directions: Cook over medium heat.
Cook most of the liquid out.

title: bundles of chicken
directions: Place each quarter chicken and half sweet potato in center of square of heavy-duty foil.
Spread softened butter over each serving. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Top with pineapple slice. Fold torn edges of foil together in tight double fold on top of food.
Fold ends up, using tight double fold.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 425°.
Serve in opened packages. Serves 4.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, oil and sugars together until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients to batter and mix well.
Roll into small balls, then roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet, 2-inches apart and press down with the sugared bottom of a glass.
Bake in 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: gator tators
directions: Use butter and Italian dressing for saute.
Cover the bottom of nonstick skillet generously with melted butter.
Slice potatoes thin in the skillet and saute.
Cover potatoes with Cajun/Creole seasoning and garlic salt.
Place lid over skillet and continue to cook on medium until all potatoes begin to blacken.
Make sure you stir often placing every slice on bottom.
Add garlic salt throughout cooking.
Should take approximately 15 to 20 minutes.

title: *marinated cole slaw
directions: Layer the cabbage, green pepper and onions in a bowl.
Bring to a boil the remaining ingredients.
Pour over cabbage.
Cover. Refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Toss and serve.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Move oven rack to lowest position.
Heat oven to 450°.
Grease a 12-inch pizza pan or cookie sheet.
Cook and stir sausage, potatoes, onion and green pepper until sausage is fully cooked. Drain.

title: chocolate fudge upside-down cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add milk.
Sift flour, salt, baking powder and cocoa together; add to creamed mixture.
Stir well and put in buttered pan.
Sprinkle with nuts and cover with mixture of brown sugar, white sugar and cocoa.
Then pour boiling water over top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tuna cashew casserole
directions: Set aside half of noodles.
Combine remaining ingredients in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle the noodles you had set aside on top, then bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Add all ingredients to sweet potatoes and mix thoroughly. Turn into greased baking dish and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes, until firm on top.
Serve hot, warm or cold, alone or with a dollop of whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: apple crunch
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients until crumbly.
Use enough sliced apples or peaches to fill a 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Spread the crumbly mixture over the fruit. Drizzle with melted butter or oleo.
Bake at 350° approximately 1/2 hour, until lightly brown.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients (except 1 hard-boiled egg). Slice remaining egg and arrange in a ring on a lettuce-lined salad plate.
Pile salad mixture onto dish.

title: baked noodles
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in and brown noodles.
Add chicken rice soup and 2 cans water.
Stir in package of onion soup mix and can of mushrooms with liquid.
Cover and simmer until liquid is absorbed.
Pour mixture into pan.
Bake in oven at 350° just until browned.

title: snipel krazen
directions: Mix
first
three
ingredients.
Gradually
add
flour. Drop tiny bits in one quart of boiling water with 1/2 teaspoon of salt. (It's important water is boiling.)
Boil
5 minutes; drain.

title: mushrooms and onions
directions: Slice mushrooms to make 2 cups.
Dice onion in small pieces. Place in skillet of melted butter.
Heat to boiling point; add water.
Turn heat to simmer for 35 minutes, stirring frequently. This is always an attractive and tasty addition to a roast, steak, pork chops, etc.

title: quick fudge
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan; line with waxed paper and butter again.
Melt chocolate chips in double boiler.
Blend in sweetened condensed milk.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Add nuts. Quickly pour into prepared pan and spread evenly.
Chill in refrigerator until firm, 2 to 3 hours.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Heat milk, rice and sugar and cook until tender.
Stir 2 or 3 times while cooking.
Take off burner and add beaten eggs.
Stir until thickened (do not cook).
If too thick, thin with a little heavy cream or milk.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.

title: fruited champagne punch
directions: Blend all fruit juices.
Add water; mix well.
Chill.
Mix early enough to allow several hours for juices to chill and flavors to blend.

title: not so sweet finger jello
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups of boiling water.
Soften 2 packages of gelatine in 1/2 cup of cold water.
Add gelatine to jello and stir until completely dissolved.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan and refrigerate.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together and let set overnight.

title: taco bean salad
directions: Layer of chopped lettuce, layer of chopped onion, layer of chopped tomatoes, layer of chili beans, layer of creamy Italian dressing, layer of cheese and layer of Doritos.
Serves 15 to 18. Serve from top layer down to bottom layer.

title: chopstick chicken
directions: Drain oranges and save 1/4 to 1/2 cup syrup.
Beat the soup until smooth.
Blend in syrup.
Place in casserole and top with noodles.
Bake at 325° for about 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6. Good doubled to serve 12 to 14.

title: ice pickles-spice
directions: Add salt to boiling water and pour over cucumbers.
Let stand 4 days. Drain and wash cucumber slices, then pour 2 quarts boiling water over cucumbers.
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain. Add alum to 2 quarts boiling water and pour over cucumbers.
Let stand 24 hours. Drain. Boil together the vinegar, sugar and spice.
Pour over pickles. Repeat for 4 days.
Pack pickles in sterilized jars and pour hot syrup on and seal.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Fold in one 8 ounce Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: hearty breakfast skillet
directions: Brown sausage.
Add potatoes and tomatoes; cook 5 minutes or until potatoes are brown.
Top with cheese.
Mix eggs and milk; pour evenly over ingredients in skillet.
Cover; reduce heat to low.
Cook 10 to 12 minutes or until eggs are set and cheese is melted.
Let stand, uncovered, 5 minutes, before cutting into pieces.

title: ham loaf(from the inn restaurant in new wilmington, pennsylvania)
directions: Mix all together.
Shape and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: spinach dip
directions: In medium bowl, blend soup mix with sour cream, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Stir in spinach and water chestnuts; chill.
Cut top off bread; set aside. Hollow out the center of the bread; cut into cubes and reserve for dipping.
The bread cubes may be toasted by baking for 5 to 10 minutes in a 350° oven.
Spoon the dip into the hollowed out bread.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine ingredients, mixing well.
Crumble in bacon before serving (optional).

title: great italian salad
directions: Wash head of lettuce.
Wrap in a paper towel to drain.
Tear into medium pieces.
Add vinegar on top and then sprinkle oil all over salad.
Add the Parmesan cheese and cut into squares the Muenster cheese along with dicing the peppers up.
Sprinkle black pepper over salad.
This is good with Italian garlic bread!

title: tapas
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; spread in a casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Combine milk and eggs together.
Mix flour gradually with the egg mixture until you have a smooth, thin batter.
Pour over the cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: lazy cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in pan.
Stir flour, milk and sugar together.
Pour batter into pan. Spread filling evenly over batter. Bake until brown.

title: pear honey
directions: Cook all ingredients together except ginger, 35 minutes or
a bit longer.
Add ginger and cook 10 minutes longer.
Put in jars and seal.
Makes 12 (1/2-pint) jars.

title: amaretto
directions: Simmer sugar and water together until a syrup is formed.
Add all other ingredients.
Makes 6 cups.

title: melt in your mouth cookies
directions: Mix powdered sugar, sugar, margarine and eggs, then add the rest of ingredients.
Put in 3 rolls for refrigerator to chill. Slice.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 dozen.

title: edible play dough
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.

title: aunt bill's candy
directions: Caramelize 2 cups sugar by melting in heavy skillet. While sugar is caramelizing, combine and bring to a boil in large saucepan, 4 cups sugar and corn syrup.
Pour caramelized sugar slowly into boiling mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook to 245° on candy thermometer, stirring frequently.
Remove from fire and immediately add soda, stirring vigorously as it foams up. Add butter and stir only until it is melted. Cool 20 minutes. Add vanilla and beat until thick and creamy. Add pecans.
Pour in buttered pan. Cool.
Cut into small squares.

title: strawberry glaze pie
directions: Mash enough strawberries to measure 1 cup.
Mix sugar and cornstarch in a 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in water and mashed strawberries.
Gradually cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Boil for 1 minute while stirring.
Cool. Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Spread on bottom of baked pie shell.
Fill shell with remaining strawberries.
Pour cooked strawberry mixture over top.
Refrigerate until set, about 3 hours.

title: eleven minute fudge
directions: Mix margarine, milk and sugar.
Cook for 11 minutes in double boiler.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows, peanut butter morsels, salt and vanilla.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan greased with butter or margarine.

title: cucumber dressing
directions: Slice cucumbers and let set in salt water an hour.
Pour off salt water.
Add sugar, white vinegar and celery seed.
Stir well. Add to cucumbers.
Will keep in refrigerator several days.

title: molasses spice crisps
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Cream the shortening, sugar, egg and molasses.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Chill 2 hours or overnight.
Roll into balls.
Dip balls in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
(Tops crack nicely.)

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix juice from asparagus with soup. In 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish, layer asparagus, crackers, soup and cheese in 2 layers, ending with cheese. Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly throughout, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: basic seeds cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Work in flour.
Add lemon peel, vanilla and seeds; blend well.
Chill for 4 hours or more.
Roll thin and cut into shapes with cookie cutter.
Bake on greased cookie sheet about 10 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Beat egg with 1 tablespoon lemon juice.
Combine flour, garlic powder and paprika.
Dip chicken in egg mixture, then in flour mixture.
In skillet, brown chicken in butter.
Dissolve bouillon in water.
Add remaining lemon juice and bouillon to chicken in skillet.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until tender.
Good alone or with rice.

title: amazing raisin cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) round pans.
In large bowl with mixer at low speed, beat first 10 ingredients 2 minutes, scraping bowl frequently.
Stir in apples, raisins and nuts.
Pour into pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove; cool. Fill and frost with 2 cups whipped cream.

title: pineapple punch
directions: Mix and freeze.
Use with 7-Up or ginger ale.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Cook at 300° for 3 hours.

title: quesadillas
directions: Heat a
lightly greased frying pan and place each tortilla in the pan.
cook until soft (do not fry or dry).
Grate cheese and place 2 to 3 tablespoons in each tortilla.
Fold in half.
Bake in oven at 350° for 3 minutes or until the cheese melts.
Serve with olives, sour cream, onions and salsa.

title: "clyde brown fun fair" fried dough
directions: Thaw bread
dough and divide into 6 pieces.
Lightly flour cutting board.
With rolling pin, flatten dough into circle or oval (do not roll dough too much).
Stretch dough with hands to make larger circles.
Let dough rise for 10 to 15 minutes.
Heat about an inch of cooking oil in electric frypan (400°).
Cook 2 to 3 pieces of fried dough at a time until brown on both sides. (Dough cooks best if only turned once.)
Drain on paper towels. Sprinkle with sugar.

title: cheese 'n egg casserole
directions: Butter bread slices and cut into 2-inch cubes.
Alternate layers of bread and cheese in greased pans.
Mix milk, dry mustard, salt, pepper, & Worcestershire sauce.
Add eggs and mix together. Pour egg mixture over cheese and bread.
Refrigerate 3-4 hrs. or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hr.

title: herbed halibut
directions: Heat the broiler; sprinkle the halibut fillets with salt and pepper and spread the mayonnaise over the top of each fillet.
Put in a shallow broiler pan and broil until the fish is just opaque, 5 to 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with the chopped parsley before serving.

title: banana icebox pudding
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on package.
Add Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk.
Make layers of wafers, bananas and pudding. Refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Stir until blended.
Bake in a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: mama's cherry nut salad
directions: Mix and bring to boil cherries, sugar and Jell-O.
Remove from heat and add pineapple and nuts.
Pour into mold and refrigerate until firm.

title: punch
directions: Mix jello, sugar and water.
Add the rest of the ingredients. Makes one gallon.
Put in freezer and freeze hard.
When needed, put in refrigerator to thaw.
Put in bowl and add two bottles of ginger ale or 7-Up.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and pepper; drain.
Add to beaten eggs and corn. Bake in greased dish; dot with butter.
Add 1/2 package Pepperidge Farm stuffing on top.
Butter the crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: apple cinnamon chicken
directions: Dip chicken into apple juice and coat with cinnamon graham cracker crumbs.
Put into baking dish with small amount of apple juice added to bottom to prevent sticking.
Bake a 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve with applesauce and your favorite vegetable.
This meal is very low fat and delicious.

title: bacon stuffed burgers
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon and discard all but 2 tablespoons drippings.
Saute onion in drippings until tender. Crumble bacon; add mushrooms to skillet and set aside.
Combine beef, pork, cheese, pepper, garlic powder and steak sauce in large bowl.
Shape into 16 patties.
Divide bacon mixture and place over eight patties.
Place remaining patties on top and press edges tightly to seal.
Grill over medium coals until well done.

title: chili-rice casserole
directions: Cut Jack into strips.
Mix sour cream and chilies.
Butter a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Season rice with salt and pepper.
Layer rice, sour cream and cheese strips in that order with rice on top. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Combine all ingredients gently by hand.
Use no other liquid. Mix well.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350° in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Do not overbake.

title: apricot nut bread
directions: Pour boiling water over apricots, sugar and butter.
Let cool. Add 2 beaten eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix into apricot mixture.
Add nuts; mix well. Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pecan pull apart
directions: In the Evening:
Spray Bundt pan with Pam.
Sprinkle chopped pecans on bottom of pan.
Put 18 frozen Rhodes rolls over nuts, then sprinkle regular butterscotch pudding over rolls.
Mix melted margarine, brown sugar and a dash of cinnamon together.
Pour over rolls.
Spray Pam over waxed paper and lay paper across pan.
Put dish towel over.
Let set overnight.

title: brunch quiche
directions: *Low-fat cheese and milk may be used.

title: barbecue wieners
directions: Cut wieners into 3 pieces.
Place in crock-pot.
Mix rest of ingredients together and pour over wieners.
Cook on high for 3 hours or until wieners swell.
Serve hot.

title: quesadillas
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Place 4 tortillas on large cookie sheet. Top each tortilla with 1/4 of the roasted red peppers, green onions, cheese and cilantro; top with remaining tortillas.

title: bud's creamy frozen fruit cups
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese and sugar until fluffy. Halve 9 cherries. Chop the remaining cherries. Set aside halved cherries and 18 oranges for garnish. Add pineapple, pecans and chopped cherries to cream cheese mixture. Fold in whipped topping and remaining oranges (can cut the oranges in half or thirds). Line muffin cups with paper or foil liners. Spoon fruit mixture into cups. Garnish with reserved cherries and oranges. Freeze until firm. Store in Ziploc bags and remove as needed from the freezer 10 minutes prior to serving. Top with mint, if desired.

title: penn-dutch sauerkraut
directions: Melt the shortening.
Add onion.
Cook until light brown. Drain the sauerkraut and rinse.
Add to onion and cook for 8 minutes.
Add caraway and potato.
Cover with boiling water.
Cook for 30 minutes, uncovered.
Add brown sugar and chopped apple. Cover and cook for 30 minutes.

title: lemon blueberry bread
directions: Beat butter, sugar, 3 tablespoons lemon juice and eggs. Combine flour, baking powder and salt; stir into egg mixture alternately with milk.
Fold in lemon peel, nuts and blueberries. Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes (until bread tests done) at 350°.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan. Prepare glaze; combine 2 tablespoons lemon juice and confectioner sugar.
Drizzle over bread.
Cool on rack.

title: old virginia wassail
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to a simmer.
Strain and serve hot with gingersnaps.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
With mixer, beat sugar and eggs for 5 minutes.
Slowly beat in oil.
Beat in flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and vanilla.
With spoon, stir in apples, raisins and nuts.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.
Remove cake from pan.

title: jalapeno jelly
directions: Remove seeds and run peppers through food grinder using fine blade.
Use all juice.
Slowly boil all ingredients for 10 minutes; remove from heat.
Add liquid pectin and boil hard 1 minute.
Pour into sterilized 1/2 pint Kerr jars to within 1/2 inch of top.
Yields five 8-ounce jars.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well.
Add mushrooms.
Let set for several hours.
Will keep in refrigerator for weeks.

title: meat pie
directions: Mix chicken, broth and celery soup in a pan; bring to a boil. Pour in a greased 13-inch dish.
Mix flour, margarine and buttermilk; pour over chicken mixture.
Cook in a 350° oven for about 45 minutes.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until brown.

title: creamed potatoes
directions: Pare and slice potatoes into uniform sized pieces into a 2-quart casserole dish (with lid).
Place salt and water in with potatoes.
Cook on High for 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender enough to cream.
Do not drain. Place casserole dish on mixer stand.
Put margarine in dish and whip, using milk gradually, until potatoes are of serving consistency.
Can be made ahead and reheated at 70% power in microwave.

title: chicken and rice nicaraguan style
directions: Boil chicken in water (6 cups).
Save the broth and make the rice; set aside.
Melt butter; saute onion, peppers and garlic until soft.
Add tomatoes and capers; simmer.
Add peas, carrots, chicken, rice and olives.
Mix thoroughly.
Top with the Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: three grain salad
directions: *Veg-it with sea salt and yeast from health food store, else use substitute, Veg-All from super market.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt together in a small bowl; set aside.
In a large bowl, beat sugar into softened butter until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, and mix in thoroughly. Blend in vanilla and lemon extracts.
Slowly mix in dry ingredients until dough is well blended.
(If you find it difficult to mix the dough to a consistency that will be easy to roll, scrape the dough into a plastic bag and knead it until it is more pliable.)
Roll our dough about one-fourth of the dough at a time.
Roll the dough to the thickness you prefer, usually 1/4 inch or less.
Cut the dough with cookie cutter.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: holiday sweet potatoes
directions: Drain peaches, reserving juice.
Dissolve cornstarch in 1/4 cup juice and set aside.
In skillet, heat remaining juice, brown sugar, cranberry sauce, cinnamon and butter.
When butter is melted, add cornstarch mixture.
Stir over medium heat until mixture thickens.
Add sweet potatoes and cook 10 minutes.
Stir in peaches and cook additional 5 minutes.

title: french fried ice cream
directions: Mix 4 parts of cornflakes to 1 part of cinnamon, coconut and sugar.
Roll ice cream ball in cornflake mixture, dip into milk, then roll back into cornflake mixture.
Freeze on wax paper for 1 to 2 hours.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Cook until it thickens, stirring often.
Cool and fold in Cool Whip.

title: orange delight cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, jello, eggs, oil and water.
Bake in 3 round cake pans at 350° for 30 minutes.
Take juice of 2 large oranges and pour over cake layers before icing.

title: waikiki meatballs
directions: Mix beef, crumbs, onion, egg, salt, ginger and milk.
Shape into meatballs.
Brown and cook in melted shortening.
Remove from pan; pour out fat.
Mix cornstarch and sugar.
Stir in pineapple syrup, vinegar and soy sauce until smooth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Add meatballs, pineapple and green pepper and heat through.
Good with rice.

title: rotel dip
directions: Brown meat; drain dry.
Melt cheese in browned meat.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes; stir to keep from sticking.
Serve with potato chips or corn chips.

title: annette's banana pudding
directions: Beat together pudding, Eagle Brand milk, evaporated milk and whole milk.
Cool Whip mixture:
Lightly stir Cool Whip and coffee creamer together. Layer vanilla wafers, bananas, pudding and whipped cream.

title: eggnog cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Beat on medium speed for 3 minutes. Pour into 3 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool completely before removing from pans.
Frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: egg casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute ham, onions and mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter until onions are tender. Add eggs and cook until slightly set. Remove from heat.

title: sombrero chocolate cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together in large mixing bowl for 4 minutes.
Pour batter into a well-greased, lightly floured Bundt pan or large tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.
Turn out on a wire rack after a few minutes to finish cooling.
Dust with confectioners sugar and with Glaze.

title: cranberry waldorf salad
directions: Mix cranberries, sugar and marshmallows and let stand overnight. The following day add apples, grapes and nuts.
Stir in whipped cream.
Chill 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: christmas morning casserole
directions: Mix and pour into shallow 11 x 8-inch casserole.
Soak overnight in refrigerator.
In the morning, preheat oven to 350° and bake uncovered for 30 minutes or until it begins to brown. Slice and serve.

title: teriyaki beef
directions: Mix ingredients in large bowl.
Add meat.
Allow to marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Serve with rice.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar together. Bring the next 4 ingredients to a boil. Pour over sugar and flour. Stir well. Add buttermilk and stir. Add eggs, baking soda and vanilla. Stir. Pour into a greased and floured jelly roll pan. Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients well with hands. Make into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes on each side.

title: vegetable bread
directions: Saute celery, green peppers and onion.
Mix biscuits and sauteed vegetables.
Add bacon bits and Cheddar cheese.
Mix well and put in greased Bundt pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mimi's sausage muffins
directions: Brown and drain sausage and mix Old English cheese and one stick margarine all together and put on English muffin halves. Freeze in heavy-duty Ziploc bags; don't thaw, just broil until bubbly.
You do not need to toast muffins before putting sausage mixture on them.

title: easy cherry dessert
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in two cans cherry pie filling. Pour box white cake mix over cherries.
Cut two sticks margarine over that; lightly sprinkle nuts over that.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli tortellini salad
directions: Cook tortellini per package directions.
Drain.
Mix other ingredients.
Pour over tortellini. Refrigerate.

title: strawberries and sour cream crepes
directions: Prepare crepes.
Combine sour cream, sugar and cinnamon (optional).
Spread crepes with an equal amount of sour cream mixture and a few sliced berries. Roll up. Sprinkle top with powdered sugar. Garnish with mint leaves and sliced strawberries.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown rice and onions in olive oil in skillet over medium heat.
Add hamburger and tomatoes.
Simmer one hour.

title: cocktail hot dogs
directions: Melt jelly in saucepan.
Add hot dogs and mustard.
Simmer 1 to 2 minutes.
Serve hot with toothpicks.

title: potatoes deluxe
directions: Mix soup with sour cream and set aside.
Thaw hash brown potatoes.
Mix diced onion, cheese, salt and pepper. Then combine the two mixtures thoroughly.
Melt margarine and turn into mixture.
Put in large baking dish.
Cover the top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Serves 12 to 15 people.

title: old fashion honey wheat bread
directions: Heat first 4 ingredients in medium saucepan until very warm. Now, add yeast.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup.
Combine warm liquid, 2 cups all-purpose flour and remaining ingredients in a large size bowl; beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
By hand, stir in remaining flour to make dough stiff.
Knead on well floured surface about 2 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl; let rise in warm place 60 minutes.
Punch down dough, divide and shape into 2 loaves.
Place in 2 greased 8 x 4-inch or 9 x 5-inch bread pans. Cover; let rise 60 minutes.
Uncover.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Immediately remove from pans; brush with butter.

title: vegetable stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter until the onion is soft, but not brown.

title: triple good bars
directions: Combine the raisins, milk and lemon juice in a medium saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, just until the mixture begins to bubble.
Remove from heat; set aside.

title: warm fruit
directions: Drain all fruits.
Add brown sugar to the juices.
Bring to a boil, then add cold water with cornstarch mixed in it to thicken. Pour over fruit.
Bake 20 minutes at 450°.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook meat and onions together in pan.
Drain.
Place in deep pan.
Add peppers, sauce and soups.
Bring to boil.

title: i can't believe it's a cookie
directions: Mix egg and sugar thoroughly.
Add peanut butter and mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Top with a chocolate star (chocolate chips can be substituted).
Press down and shape.
Bake in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cool on sheet for 1 to 2 minutes before removing.

title: barbecue beans casserole
directions: Crumble hamburger and sausage in skillet, add onion and fry over medium heat until meat is cooked; drain excess grease off.

title: pineapple pears
directions: Cook pears until tender, then grind or chop in small pieces. Mix all the ingredients and bring to slow boil; cook for 30 minutes.
Stir often.
Put in jars and seal.
Delicious with meats.

title: butterscotch brownies(bar cookie)
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Mix sugar and butter until blended; cool. Stir in egg. Measure flour and sift with baking powder and salt; blend in. Mix in vanilla and walnuts. Spread in well-greased square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inches. Bake 25 minutes. Do not overbake! Cut into bars while warm. Makes about 18 bars.

title: lemon cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese until very soft.
Gradually blend in 1/2 cup milk until smooth and creamy.
Add remaining milk and the pudding mix.
Mix at slow speed 1 minute.
Pour into cooled graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs on top.

title: cheesecake brownies
directions: Melt baking chocolate and butter in saucepan; mix well. Beat in 2 cups sugar, 3 eggs, and vanilla until blended. Stir in flour. Spread batter in prepared pan.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan in warm oven just to melt, about 3 minutes.
Beat eggs in a large bowl; mix in flour, baking powder and salt.
Squeeze thawed spinach very dry and add to egg mixture along with melted butter, chilies and cheeses.
Pour mixture into pan and bake 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes to set.
Do not overbake or it will be dry.

title: grandma thrashers oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together Crisco, brown sugar, white sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda, oatmeal and coconut.
Mix and make into balls; flatten.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken lickin' good pork chops
directions: Dredge pork chops in mixture of flour, salt, dry mustard and garlic powder.
Heat vegetable oil in skillet; add chops, sprinkle with lemon pepper and brown on both sides.
Place pork chops in crockpot; pour undiluted soup over chops.
Cover and cook on LOW 8 hours or on HIGH 6 hours.
Serve with hot cooked rice.

title: avocado ranch soup
directions: In blender, combine milk, yogurt, mayonnaise, chicken broth, salad dressing mix and avocado chunks.
Puree until smooth.
Pour mixture into large bowl.
Stir in tomato, cucumber and onion. Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Garnish each bowl with avocado slices before serving.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, lemon juice and sweetened condensed milk and pour over vanilla wafers in pie pan.
Let set.

title: honey dressing for fruit
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Mix with honey, vinegar, lemon juice and onion.
Add oil gradually, beating smoothly.
Makes about 2 cups or dressing.

title: crab mac salad
directions: Cook elbow macaroni (per directions on package). Drain macaroni.
Run cold water over it and drain again. Add imitation crab, diced celery, diced onion and Old Bay seasoning.
Mix thoroughly.
Add mayonnaise and chill before serving.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: four vegetable relish
directions: Wash, trim and quarter vegetables.
Put vegetables through food grinder using coarse blade; drain, discarding liquid. Combine vinegar and remaining ingredients in large saucepan; heat to boiling.
Add vegetables; simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Continue simmering while quickly packing one clean, hot jar at a time.
Fill to within 1/2-inch of top, making sure vinegar solution covers vegetables.
Cap each jar at once. Process 5 minutes in boiling water bath.
Makes 5 to 6 pints.

title: crisp oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, then add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Form into balls.
Bake at 375° until done, about 10 or 12 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Add onion and celery; cook until tender and drain.
Stir in soup, salt, catsup and pepper.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Spoon over warm bun halves and sprinkle with cheese.

title: russian tea
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Store in covered container.
Mix by adding 1 tablespoon per cup of hot water.
Serve hot.

title: milk lefsa
directions: Heat milk and margarine to boiling hot. Just before it starts to boil, sift flour, salt and sugar.
Pour hot milk slowly into flour mixture. Mix well and make into balls. Put on wax paper and cover with damp cloth. Roll each ball thin and bake on lefsa iron.

title: caramel icing
directions: Cook on medium heat until boiling. Then cook only 2 minutes. Beat with mixer until of spreading consistency.
(Add vanilla.) Double recipe to frost sides of cake!

title: fresh broccoli soup
directions: Cut broccoli into small pieces.
Steam with 1 cup water until tender.
In a double boiler melt 1/2 cup butter and flour to make a roux.
Add chicken stock, salt and pepper.
Cook until thick.
Add half and half and cooked broccoli.
Heat thoroughly.

title: green pea casserole
directions: Saute:
celery or cream of celery soup, onions and green peppers.
In a casserole dish put peas, mushroom soup, pimiento and water chestnuts.
Mix well.
Pour both mixtures in a casserole dish along with reserved juice from peas.
Top with bread crumbs or crackers.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Butter Pyrex baking pan, put layer of asparagus.
Blend soup with cheese sauce and pour over asparagus.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick wiener casserole
directions: In skillet, fry wieners until light brown.
Pour undiluted vegetable soup over wieners.
Heat.
Transfer to lightly greased small casserole.
Top with mashed potatoes; finally top with cheese and heat in oven until cheese is melted.

title: cranberry orange bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease loaf pan.
Mix dry ingredients together; set aside.
Beat eggs, milk, sugar, orange juice and rind and oil.
Add to flour mixture and mix just enough to moisten flour. Stir in cereal, cranberries and nuts. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes. Cool in pan for 10 minutes, remainder on rack.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake
cake
according to directions.
In saucepan, cook pineapple (with
juice) and sugar over medium heat until thick and syrupy
(20 to 25 minutes).
Stir occasionally.
When cake is done,
poke
holes	with fork 1 inch apart.
Pour pineapple over cake and spread.
Cool completely.

title: prune cake(very good)
directions: Mix dry ingredients and oil.
Add milk, eggs, prunes and nuts. Bake in 3 layers or 1 long pan at 350°.
Cook until done.

title: goodie's bbq rub
directions: Mix all together and use as a dry rub before cooking ribs or chicken.

title: chicken paickas
directions: Brown onion in shortening.
Add seasoning and chicken.
Brown 10 minutes.
Add water and let simmer slowly until tender.
Remove chicken; add sour cream to drippings in pan and mix well.
Add dumplings; arrange chicken on top.
Heat through and serve.

title: deep dish blueberry cobbler
directions: Mix and beat ingredients in small mixing bowl at low speed until particles are fine.
Sprinkle on top of filling.

title: cheese casserole
directions: Slightly beat eggs.
Add other ingredients in order given, reserving 2 tablespoons bread crumbs and 1 tablespoon cheese.
Mix these together.
Place first mixture in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and sprinkle the crumb/cheese mixture on top.
Bake in oven at 375° for 40 minutes or until brown.

title: bread pudding
directions: Tear up toast into bite size pieces.
Put into buttered baking dish.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and sugar in a bowl.
Beat well and pour over toast.
Sprinkle well with cinnamon and sugar on top. Slice small slices of butter on top.
Bake at 350° to 400°.

title: pineapple beets
directions: Stir cornstarch into 1/2 cup pineapple juice.
Make smooth paste.
Add rest of pineapple juice, sugar and vinegar.
Stir. Place in double boiler and cook until thick and clear, 8 minutes. Add oleo and crushed pineapple.
Drain beets.
Cut into sections. Add to pineapple mixture and heat well and serve.

title: potato balls
directions: Mash potatoes; add flour as needed to keep potato stuck together, the potatoes need to stay dry; make into firm balls, put into boiling water and boil for 1/2 hour, stir occasionally to keep from sticking.
Remove from pan and serve with gravy and smoked neck bones.

title: shrimp or crab bisque
directions: Over low heat, cook onions in butter. Add shell fish and all other ingredients, except parsley and egg. Bring to boiling point. Sprinkle sieved egg and chopped parsley in bottom of soup bowls. Pour biscuit on top and serve piping hot.

title: sheet party mix
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
In a medium sized bowl, combine orange juice concentrate, water, egg white, honey, cinnamon and nutmeg. Add nuts 1/2 cup at a time, stirring until well coated.
With a slotted spoon, remove nuts, draining off excess liquid.
Spread nuts on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake, stirring occasionally, for 30 minutes or until nuts are fairly dry and golden.
Cool on wax paper.
Store in a tightly covered container.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix all together and pour into a greased square cake pan and bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: orange punch
directions: Make Kool-Aid as directed, using 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Add other juices, stirring well.
Freeze until mushy.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: lazy cobbler
directions: Melt butter in deep baking pan. Pour peaches in pan. In small bowl, mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Pour milk in and stir well. Pour batter over top of peaches and bake for 45 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Melt Jell-O in pineapple over medium heat until Jell-O dissolves, then cool.
Add buttermilk and let partially set.
Add Cool Whip and nuts.

title: venison roast
directions: Place all vegetables in bottom of crock-pot.
Add roast, then soup and salt and then water.
Cook overnight or all day in crock-pot on low.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat margarine and sugar.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients and mix.
Stir in oats. Drop by tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 minutes at 375°.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: In bowl, mix together all ingredients.
Put into a bowl and let set like Jell-O.

title: ginny's popovers
directions: Beat all together.
Put into well-greased muffin tins in cold oven.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin swirl cheesecake
directions: Combine
crumbs
and
margarine;
press onto bottom and sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Combine Neufchatel cheese, 1/2
cup sugar and vanilla, mixing at medium speed on electric mixer
until well
blended.
Add
eggs, one at a time, mixing well
after each
addition.
Reserve
1 cup Neufchatel cheese mixture;
add pumpkin, remaining sugar and spices to remaining Neufchatel cheese
mixture.
Mix well.
Layer half of pumpkin mixture
and half
of
Neufchatel
cheese mixture over crust. Repeat
layers. Cut
through
batter with knife several times for
marble effect. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Loosen cake from rim of pan; cool before removing rim of pan.
Chill.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef and drain.
In a large pot, add all ingredients. Simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: vegetarian lentil barley soup
directions: Place all ingredients except spinach in large kettle.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring occasionally for 50 minutes or until lentils and barley are crisp-tender
Add spinach; cook 10 minutes or until lentils and barley are tender.
If too thick, add water. Makes 5 quarts.
May be frozen.

title: mrs. irene's apple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks; beat until light.
Add flour to which has been added the spices, then add stiffly beaten egg whites, raisins, nuts and other fruits.
Bake very slowly as fruit cake.

title: grandma's breakfast fruit
directions: In a saucepan, combine apples, prunes, raisins, orange and 3 cups water.

Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes. Stir in sugar and cinnamon. Combine cornstarch and remaining water. Stir into saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Cook for 2 minutes. Chill.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: hazelnut cheesecake
directions: Grease spring-form pan.
Chop nuts and place in bottom of pan as crust.
Beat cheese.
Add sugar, flour and salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Add eggs.
Stir in chocolate chips, liqueur and vanilla.
Pour into pan.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken breasts with seasoning until tender. Remove all bones and cut chicken into fairly small pieces. Cook broccoli about 5 minutes in boiling water. Drain and arrange broccoli in a shallow greased baking dish.
Place chicken on top of broccoli. Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle cheese and bread crumbs, which have been mixed with melted butter, over all. Garnish with pimiento.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: corn and mac bake
directions: In a greased baking dish put 1 can whole kernel corn (do not drain) and 1 can cream style corn.
Add one stick melted oleo, cheddar cheese and macaroni.
Mix and bake at 350 degrees until it is bubbly and set.

title: pound cake cookies
directions: Cream butter with sugar. Blend in other ingredients. Roll into small balls.
Flatten with fork.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 300°.

title: chicken and dumplings(serves 4)
directions: In 12-inch skillet, over medium-high heat, heat oil.
Add chicken and cook about 5 minutes, stirring frequently until golden brown.
Add mushrooms and season with garlic powder and pepper. Cook about 5 minutes, stirring frequently until tender.
Remove mixture to bowl and keep warm.
In same skillet, over medium heat, melt margarine.
Add flour and cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly until mixture is golden brown.
Add instant chicken broth and gradually stir in 3 cups of water.
Cook about 10 minutes, stirring constantly until mixture is smooth and slightly thickened.
Add carrots and peas to skillet along with chicken and mushrooms. Bring to a boil, covered.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pat out on wax paper-lined cookie sheets 1/2 inch thick.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Cut into serving size pieces.
Roll in flour.
Brown in hot fat.
Place in roasting pan and cover with mushroom soup.
Bake, covered, at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: berry pie
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil, stirring constantly until thickens and is clear.
Add Jell-O; stir until dissolved.
Take off stove and cool.
Then add 1 quart of berries.
Pour into prepared pie crust (graham cracker crust is excellent).

title: tuna supper with cheddar sauce
directions: In a medium saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in flour; cook and stir over low heat for 1 minute.
Raise heat to medium. Gradually stir in milk.
Cook and stir until mixture boils and thickens.
Remove from heat.
Add Cheddar cheese, stirring until melted.
Stir in tuna, macaroni and pepper.
Heat until hot. Serve sprinkled with chopped parsley.

title: ada's vegetable chili
directions: In a 5 qt. pot combine celery, carrots, beans and soup.
Fill soup cans with water and add to pot.
Cook over low heat.
In a large skillet, brown beef, stirring frequently to keep in small pieces.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Empty skillet into pot. In same skillet, brown peppers and onions.	Add to pot.
Simmer pot over low heat, stirring occasionally at least 4 hrs.
The longer the better.	1 hr. before serving, add diced potatoes and cook until tender.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes in a greased and floured sheet cake pan.

title: puppy chow mix
directions: Melt butter; add chips and peanut butter.
Pour over cereal and mix until coated.
Spread out on waxed paper to dry.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Store in sealed container.

title: sweet sour salad
directions: Blend sugar, vinegar, oil, paprika and salt well.
Mix all vegetables and add blended ingredients.
Let stand at least 6 hours or overnight.
Drain and add 2 hard-boiled eggs to garnish.

title: perfect biscuits
directions: Mix well and roll out to cut small.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes.

title: squash fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop in hot oil and fry until crispy.

title: caramel bars
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients in a bowl and then pat into a 9 x 13 pan. Bake for 13 minutes at 350°.

title: corn corn bread
directions: Chop onion, bell pepper, cheese and pimento fine.
In large bowl, mix all ingredients; stir together.
Grease pan and pour mixture into baking pan.
Bake for 40 minutes at 375°.

title: joyce's baked spinach
directions: Cook spinach.
Drain well and squeeze out excess liquid.
Saute onions in butter.
Mix spinach, onion, Parmesan and sour cream. Pour into casserole dish and top with buttered cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except dressing mix.
Put 1/2 mixture in baking dish.
Add layer of dressing mix.
Add last half of mixture and cover with herb dressing mix.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sandy's peach cakesocorro, new mexico
directions: Sift or mix dry cake mix into ungreased 13 X 9 pan.
Mix in 16 oz. of moisture (use juice from peaches plus enough water to make 16 oz.) in the pan.
Place peach slices on top of cake batter then press down.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serve warm with either Cool Whip or vanilla ice cream.

title: chicken noodle amandine
directions: Melt 1/4 cup butter in a saucepan over medium heat.
Add almonds and stir until lightly browned.
Remove from heat.
Set aside.
Melt remaining butter in a clean saucepan over medium heat.
Add mushrooms and saute for 3 minutes.
Add orange peel, salt, pepper, chicken broth and chicken.
Continue cooking an extra minute.
Stir sour cream into chicken mixture; heat through but do not boil.
Serve immediately over hot noodles.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: classic sour cream cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine crumbs and margarine.
Press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: french country eggs
directions: Partially pre-cook bacon.
Line bottom of casserole with one-half of bacon strips.
Break six eggs and space them evenly on top of the bacon strips. Surround each egg with a thin circle of heavy cream.
Top with grated cheese.
Repeat second layer on top of first, using remaining bacon and eggs.
Bake in preheated oven for 20 minutes at 325°.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Toss with the mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar mixture.
Marinate in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: christmas tree vegetable tray
directions: Place the clean leaf lettuce onto a plate.
Arrange the broccoli florets into a Christmas tree shape.
Using other vegetables decorate the tree.
Examples include:
Red pepper (julienned slices) as garland on the tree.
Cauliflower as the trunk with a border of carrot and celery sticks.
Serve with Ranch dressing as dip.

title: annette's potato salad
directions: In large pot, boil 6 cups water.
Add potatoes and cook 20 to 25 minutes.
Drain water and cool for 15 minutes.
In large bowl, add remaining ingredients with potatoes and toss gently.
Add additional mayonnaise, if needed, and refrigerate.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pretty darn good bean dip
directions: Combine everything in a crock-pot or fondue pot on low for a couple of hours.
Stir every now and again.
Enjoy on corn chips.

title: custard cream pie with graham cracker crust
directions: Mix crackers, sugar and margarine.
Reserve 1/4 cup for topping.
Press in 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°.

title: soft spicy bars
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add egg.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg, salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture alternating with molasses and milk; add raisins or dates.
Spread on greased cookie sheet and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cut in bars.

title: german oven pancake(island style)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Using a wire whip or beater, beat each egg separately.
Combine first 4 ingredients.
In 12-inch skillet, melt butter until just melted.
Add the batter and cook for just 1 minute.
Place in oven and bake for 20 minutes or until golden brown and very puffy.

title: southern green beans
directions: Fry bacon in a medium pot; add water, beans and onion.
Simmer for 40 minutes or until beans are tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: ground beef and macaroni casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and drain. Cook macaroni until done and drain. Add macaroni and rest of ingredients to the ground beef. Heat until thoroughly warm.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread each ingredient out in layers in an oblong baking dish, each layer on top of the last one.
Place butter slices here and there in their layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: hamburger harvest casserole
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine beef, onions, tomatoes with liquid and Worcestershire sauce.
Spoon into a greased 3-quart casserole dish.
Layer potatoes, flour, corn, lima beans and green peppers on top.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and continue baking, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: shourbat laban(yoghurt soup)
directions: Wash meat and place in a saucepan with 6 cups of water.
Cook over low heat for 1 hour.
Add rice to meat 20 minutes before the meat is completely cooked.
Mix the yoghurt with the flour and dried mint.
Add to meat and rice mixture.
Season and stir occasionally.
Meanwhile, melt the butter.
Stir in the paprika and saute a little over low heat.
Add to the soup and serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix in large bowl.
Will serve approximately 30.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs in a mixer on low speed.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Sift together dry ingredients, add to first mixture and beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into 2 well-greased and floured 8 x 8-inch cake pans or one (9 x 13-inch) greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: onion swiss steak
directions: Cut round steak into serving pieces; season with salt and pepper and place in slow cooker.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over top and pour tomatoes over all.
Cover and cook on low, 8 to 10 hours or high for 4 hours.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Peel and chop broccoli; chop onions and eggs.
Mix with Marie's salad dressing.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients until well mixed.
Sift next 4 ingredients together.
Add to first mixture along with frozen orange juice.
Fold in oats, nuts and raisins.
Bake on ungreased cookie pan 8 to 10 minutes in a 350° oven.
Drop by teaspoon.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine sugar and corn syrup.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter.
Pour this mixture over corn flakes and coconut.
Mix well. Drop on wax paper and let cool.

title: quick and easy meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly. Put into 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan and spread catsup on top.

Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or microwave, covered with wax paper, on Medium for 30 minutes. This can be made up the night before, covered and put in the refrigerator and popped into microwave.

title: calico salad
directions: Combine vegetables in large bowl and toss lightly.
Combine sugar, flour, mustard and salt in small saucepan.
Gradually add vinegar.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until smooth and thickened.
Pour hot mixture over vegetables and stir gently. Cover and chill overnight.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients. Beat together milk, eggs and butter or oleo. Stir liquids into corn mixture and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Drain corn.
Mix all ingredients with corn and put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Stir before serving.

title: bacon and creamed topped tomatoes
directions: In a large skillet, fry bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towel and crumble.
Combine bacon and blend with sour cream.
Cut ends off tomatoes and cut tomatoes in half.
Saute cut side of tomatoes in bacon drippings.
Turn over.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Top with sour cream mixture.
Cover. Saute 2 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: indian fried bread(sopaipillas)
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder in large bowl.
Add lard or shortening to dry ingredients and mix well with hands.
Gradually add water making sure dough does not become sticky but results in doughy pliable texture.
If dough gets too sticky, sprinkle with flour.
Form 6 to 8 balls.
Roll out with rolling pin.
Cut in 4 pieces.
Fry in 1 1/2-inch oil or shortening.
Prick once in middle before frying.

title: pasta oklla norma
directions: Thinly slice and fry eggplant in olive oil, a few slices at a time.
Place slices on paper towel to dry.
In the same oil, saute garlic and then add tomato sauce.
Simmer for a few minutes and then add the eggplant.
Pour sauce on pasta, sprinkle with Parmesan and serve.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients at once. Beat well. Grease and flour pans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour 15 minutes for large pans and 1 hour for small pans. Use 2 large loaf pans or 3 small loaf pans.

title: going shopping stew
directions: Dice potatoes, carrots, parsnips and celery to desired size.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Beat pumpkin, milk, cinnamon, nutmeg, eggs, sugar and ginger together. Put into a greased 9 x 13 inch pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly over mixture. Pour melted margarine over cake mix and sprinkle nuts on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Better if made the day before.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Dissolve first 3 ingredients in hot water.
Cool.
Add pineapple (undrained).
Place in refrigerator until almost set, then fold in Cool Whip.

title: krispy kritters
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until melted.
Cook over low heat for 3 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Add cereal; stir until well coated.
Using buttered spatula, press mixture into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: apple tart
directions: Combine flour and salt in a medium bowl.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Add 3 tablespoons water, mixing to form ball.
Let stand in lightly floured cloth for 1 hour.
Roll until thin on floured surface.
Line buttered and floured 10-inch pie pan with dough. Cut to fit and prick bottom with fork.
Arrange apples slightly, overlapping on dough.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown.
Spread jelly over hot apples.

title: creamy banana pie
directions: Soften gelatine in cold water; set aside.
In a saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Blend in the milk and egg yolks.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly, about 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in softened gelatine until dissolved.
Stir in butter and vanilla. Cover the surface of custard with plastic wrap and chill until no longer warm.
Slice 3 bananas.
Fold into custard with whipped cream.
Spoon into pie shell.
Chill until set, about 4 to 5 hours.

title: cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage, onion and green pepper.
Place in a large covered container, adding sugar and salt.
Set aside.

title: sweet potato bake
directions: Cook potatoes unpeeled for 30 minutes, then peel and mash, adding sugar, butter, pineapple, cinnamon, pecans and a pinch of salt.
Coat casserole with butter.
Fill with potato mixture.
Put small marshmallows on top.
Cover; bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° until done.

title: oven beef burgundy
directions: Blend soy sauce with flour in a baking dish which has a capacity of 2 1/2 to 3 quarts.
Cut the meat into 1 1/2-inch cubes, add to soy sauce mixture and potatoes to coat the meat cubes.

title: new west chicken salad(low fat-calorie-cholesterol)
directions: Blend mayonnaise, ginger, celery and onions. Add chicken, grapes and walnuts.

title: dark secret pudding
directions: Beat eggs, milk, flour and sugar together.
Add nuts, dates and vanilla.
Bake in a slow 350° oven until solid or try with knife.
If knife comes out clean, pudding is done.
A loaf tin is preferred.

title: pumpkin swirl bread
directions: Combine cream cheese until well-blended with sugar and egg. Set aside.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add combined pumpkin, margarine, egg and water, mixing just until moistened.
Reserve 2 cups pumpkin batter.
Pour remaining batter into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch long pan.
Pour cream cheese mixture over pumpkin batter.
Top with rest of pumpkin batter.
Cut through batters with knife several times and swirl.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until pick comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes. Remove from pan.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: cabbage patch soup
directions: Mix all together and cook in crock-pot on low for 2 to 3 hours.
Delicious and low-cal.

title: chicken wings
directions: Rinse chicken wings and pat dry. Mix soy sauce, mustard, brown sugar and garlic powder together. Marinate wings in mixture overnight (or about 6 hours). Bake wings on cookie sheet for 1 hour at 375°. Baste wings occasionally with sauce. Serves 9-12.

title: slow cooked lemon chicken breasts
directions: Rinse Chicken and pat dry.
Combine Oregano, Seasoned Salt and Pepper.
Rub over Chicken.
In a skillet, brown Chicken in Butter; transfer to a slow cooker.
Add Water, Lemon Juice, Garlic and Bouillon to skillet, bring to a boil to loosen browned bits.
Pour over Chicken in slow cooker.
Add Parsley, cover and cook for 4 hours or until chicken is cooked through.
Juice may be thickened if desired and poured over Chicken and Noodles.
Yields:
6 servings.

title: ham roll-ups(appetizers)
directions: Parboil asparagus; remove from heat while still crisp, then cool.
Cut ham in half or thirds and spread with cream cheese. After cooling, put asparagus on the ham and cheese mixture and roll up.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mash bananas in mixing bowl.
Mix in remaining ingredients. Bake in loaf pans at 325° for 1 hour.

title: oven cassoulet
directions: In non-stick saucepan, sprayed with non-stick cooking spray, cook and stir the sausage, onion, carrots, celery and garlic for 4-5 min. or until onion is tender.
Stir in the tomatoes, broth, bay leaf, thyme, pepper and cloves.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered for about 15 min. or until carrots are tender and liquid is slightly thickened.
Discard bay leaf.
Stir in beans.
Transfer to a 2 qt. baking dish, sprayed.
Combine the bread crumbs, butter and parsley.
Sprinkle over sausage mixture. Bake uncovered at 350° for 30-35 min.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy ham and potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in water until tender.
Layer in bottom of glass casserole.
Lay cheese slices on top, then onion slices and top with ham.
Cover and bake 10 to 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: old fashioned egg custard
directions: Beat together lightly.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg on top.
Cook at 275° until custard sets.
When knife blade comes out clean, remove from oven at once.

title: danish lettuce salad
directions: Put lettuce on platter.
Top with the celery.
Place onion slices over all.

title: butterscotch toffee heavenly delight
directions: Whip cream until it starts to thicken. Add butterscotch syrup and vanilla slowly and continue beating until thick. Cut cake into 3 layers horizontally. Spread the butterscotch mixture on the layers and sprinkle each generously with crushed toffee. Put cake back together again and frost the top and sides with butterscotch mixture and sprinkle them, too, with toffee. Place cake in the refrigerator and chill for a minimum of 6 hours. Serves 12.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Wash potatoes and prick several times with a fork; bake at 400° for 1 hour or until done.
Let cool.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise, then scoop out pulp.
Melt butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add all-purpose flour, stirring constantly. Gradually add 6 cups milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Add potato pulp, salt, pepper, 2 tablespoons green onions, 1/2 cup bacon and 1 cup cheese.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Stir in sour cream.

title: chicken 'n' rice casserole
directions: Cook rice in boiler with salt to taste.
Add deboned chicken to drained rice.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Place in casserole dish and bake until bubbly at 400°.

title: artichoke dip
directions: *Any of the ingredients can be substituted with low fat items if desired.

title: baked hamburger and macaroni
directions: Brown hamburger; pour off fat. Cook macaroni in boiling, salted water for 8 minutes. Stir occasionally. Add cheese mix from macaroni dinner to drained macaroni. Add mushroom soup and hamburger. Stir well. Sprinkle crackers on top. Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°. Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: pork chop potato bake
directions: Go to the yard. Cut 6 tree tops. Pull up any weeds. Get Mom's soup pot. Add some dirt and earth worm. Stir and dump on your sisters head.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook spaghetti to directions on package. Set aside until cool. Chop and dice celery, green onion, cucumber, tomatoes, pepper and black olives.
Add to cooled spaghetti.
Add Parmesan cheese and salad dressing.

title: miniature wiener wellingtons
directions: Peel casing from liverwurst; slice meat into 8 slices.
Cut each slice into 4 strips.
Trim strips to fit frankfurters. Combine cheese and onion salt.
Roll liverwurst strips in cheese mixture.
Slice frankfurters 3/4 of the way through lengthwise. Stuff with liverwurst.
Unroll crescent dough and separate into 6 (1/2-inch) strips.
Wrap the strips around frankfurters.
Place rolls, seam side down, on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: whiskey slush
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except 7-Up; freeze.
To make 1 drink, put 2 to 3 tablespoonfuls of mix in highball glass with an ice cube and fill glass with 7-Up.
Mix well.
A maraschino cherry may be added for color.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Dissolve both jellos in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Add pineapple and banana.
Pour into casserole or salad mold and let gel.
Combine sugar and flour and add juice gradually, then beaten egg.
Cook until cool and spread over jello mixture.
Soften cream cheese and mix with small Cool Whip.
Spread on top of filling mixture.

title: tastees
directions: Mix beef, ketchup, mustard, horseradish, salt, pepper, etc. and add to beef; stir.
Fill same cup with water and add.
Cook on low heat, stirring constantly, 15 minutes.
Increase heat slowly until it boils.
Boil 25 minutes, stirring often.
Simmer as long as you like.
Drain off grease.
You may add cheese if you like.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Marinate chicken overnight in dressing.
Place the rice in a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Mix soup and water together and then mix well into uncooked rice.
Sprinkle the dry Lipton onion soup mix over rice mixture.
Place marinated chicken breasts (skin side up) over rice mixture.
Bake at 450° for 1 hour, covered with foil.
Remove foil and bake 15 minutes more, until browned.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix all together. Drop by spoonfuls on greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Don't overbake.

title: enchiladas
directions: Mix soups and enchilada sauce together well.
Brown hamburger and drain.
Shred the Cheddar cheese.
Mix 1/2 of the cheese with hamburger.
Spread a small amount of sauce on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Fill tortillas with hamburger mixture. Place evenly in casserole dish.
Cover with the remaining sauce and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and mix well.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar completely.
Combine flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and sift.
Add dry ingredients to sugar mixture alternately with eggs.
Beat after each addition.
Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Stir.
Fold in nuts, coconut, raisins and apples. Put in greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle butterscotch morsels on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
(I always bake it about 15 minutes longer.
Test for doneness.
You may need to let it cook longer.)
Remove from pan and cool.

title: pineapple ham patties
directions: Combine
ham,
crumbs, cloves and egg.
Mix thoroughly. Form into patties.
Arrange pineapple slices in shallow baking pan. Place a ham patty
on
each
ring.
Add pineapple juice. Bake in hot oven at
about
25 minutes or until browned. (Excellent for leftover ham.)

title: dump cake
directions: Pour pie filling in a glass 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add crushed pineapple.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over top of fruit.
Pour liquid Butter Buds on top.
(Try to pour liquid evenly over cake mix so all of cake mix is moistened.)
Bake at 350° until golden brown (approximately 40 minutes).
Top with Cool Whip and serve warm.

title: burgundy beef
directions: Fry peeled whole onions in bacon drippings until brown; remove to separate dish.
Cut beef into 1-inch cubes and saute in drippings.
When nicely browned, sprinkle 1 1/2 tablespoons flour and a pinch of thyme, marjoram, salt and pepper.
Add 1/2 cup bouillon and 1 cup wine.
Stir mixture well, then let simmer slowly (barely bubble).
If liquid boils away, add more bouillon and wine (1 part stock to 2 parts wine).
When meat has cooked 3 3/4 hours, add onions and 1 pound mushrooms.
Cook 1 more hour or until tender.
Gravy should be thick and dark brown.
Serve over rice.

title: alaskan rhubarb pineapple crisp
directions: In greased 8-inch square baking dish, mix pineapple and rhubarb; sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar.
In small bowl, mix remaining sugar, flour, oats, margarine, cinnamon and salt until crumbly.
Sprinkle over fruit.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Rhubarb was a favorite of my mom.

title: chicken-n-dumplings
directions: In skillet, saute onion and margarine.
Add flour and salt. Then add broth, water and hot pepper sauce.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Stir in chicken and vegetables.
Add sour cream.

title: mandarin cream frosting
directions: For the Mandarin Cream Frosting, beat together butter and salt in a small bowl until fluffy.
Beat in confectioners sugar alternately with mandarin syrup until smooth and spreadable.
Fold in grated mandarin rind.

title: fire house beans
directions: Cook onion, celery and green pepper.
Then add ground beef and cook.
Drain fat off meat mixture; add to beans and all other ingredients.
Simmer about 45 minutes.
Much better when beans set overnight.

title: squash dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes in preheated oven at 375°.

title: raspberry almond torte cookies
directions: Chop almonds very fine or grind in blender or processor into coarse nut flour.
Buzz oats into coarse flour.
Combine dry ingredients in bowl.
Whip oil and maple syrup together.
Add wet to dry ingredients.
Mix until well coated.
Form walnut sized balls and place on oiled cookie sheet.
Press thumb gently in center, creating space for filling.
Fill each cookie with 1/2 teaspoon raspberry preserves.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cheeses, mixing well until blended.
Add rest of ingredients, except pecans.
Roll into ball.
Refrigerate. When cold, roll in chopped nuts.
Better when served at room temperature.

title: hungarian casserole
directions: Cook noodles as on package.
Drain.
Brown meat.
Stir in tomato sauce, then remove from heat.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts in pot of water with bouillon cubes for about 1/2 hour.
Chop broccoli into small pieces and cook as usual.
Cook rice.
Saute onion in margarine.
Tear chicken into small pieces.
Combine all cooked ingredients and place in casserole.
Slice pieces of Velveeta cheese and lay on top of ingredients.
Cook at 350° for 15 minutes, stirring once.
Serves 4.

title: apple cake
directions: Bake for 45 minutes at 325° with pan of water under it.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken and take off bone.
Cut up and put in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cut up boiled eggs over it.
Add vegetables, drained.
Mix soup and broth together.
Pour over mixture.
Melt butter and add milk and flour.
Beat with mixer until blended. Pour over other mixture and bake at 300° for 15 minutes, then bake at 375° for 30 minutes until brown.

title: mary lou's pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients and put aside.
Blend oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat after each one.
Add pumpkin, water, vanilla and flour mixture.
Stir in dates and nuts.
Bake in 4 greased and floured 1-pound coffee cans (fill about 2/3 full) for 1 hour at 350°.
Check at 45 minutes.
Rest on sides when cooling in cans.

title: penuche candy
directions: Boil first 2 ingredients to the soft ball stage.
Cool and beat until it begins to thicken.
Add pecan meats.
Pour into buttered plates.
Cut when firm.

title: chicken puffs
directions: Blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons of butter until smooth. Add next 4 ingredients.
Separate rolls into 4 rectangles.
Press perforations to seal.
Spoon about 1/2 cup of chicken mixture into center of each rectangle.
Pull 4 corners of dough to top center. Twist slightly and seal edges.
Brush top with remaining butter. Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake on cookie sheet at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: blueberry cream cheese salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add pineapple and blueberry pie filling.
Mix and let chill until set.
Mix together cream cheese, sour cream, vanilla and sugar.
Spread over gelatin mixture.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: banana pudding
directions: Beat pudding and milk for 2 minutes. Add sour cream and mix together. Stir in about 1/2 to 3/4 of Cool Whip. Beat vanilla wafers in a Ziploc bag to form crumbs. Slice bananas into thin, horizontal slices. Layer crumbs, banana slices and pudding mixture. Top with Cool Whip. Sprinkle vanilla wafer crumbs on top. Store in refrigerator.

title: lima bean-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and lima beans in a large pan according to package directions.
(I use less water than called for on the package.)
While the frozen food is cooking, combine onion soup mix, sour cream, water chestnuts and mushroom soup in a casserole dish or large mixing bowl.
Drain the lima beans and broccoli. Pour into the sour cream mixture and fold together.
Melt the margarine in a large pan.
To the melted casserole add the Rice Krispies and stir to coat.
Spread on top of the casserole.
Can be frozen at this point or bake at 350°, uncovered, until bubbly, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat.
Add milk.
Tear bread into small pieces and add to mixture.
Then add drained pineapple.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in 1-quart casserole.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients
and
stir
until well blended. Grease 2 (9-inch) pie
plates;
divide mixture evenly and pour in pie plates.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: diabetic oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together ingredients except raisins.
Add raisins.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Refrigerate after they are cooled.

title: brown sugar rolls
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and mix well.
Add beaten eggs.
Sift flour, soda and tartar; add to mixture.
Add nuts.
(This makes a very stiff dough that may need to be kneaded some by hand and/or add water.)
Chill dough at least 1 hour.
Form dough into rolls. Refrigerate or freeze.
Slice and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fruits in brandy
directions: Place 1/2 of apricots in bottom of decorative 2 cup jar, making sure the top layer is flat and even.
Make second layer of cherries.
Repeat to top of jar.
You should have a "striped" effect.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: You will need muffin pans.

title: brunswick stew(low-fat)
directions: Combine all ingredients; cook until blended.
Freezes well.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Cook chicken with onions and celery.
Cool chicken.
Remove from bone and cut into bite size pieces.
Melt butter and add to dry cornbread stuffing mix.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, layer the stuffing mix with chicken.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Next day, make cake.
Split layers into 4 thin layers.
Spread frosting between each layer and on top. Refrigerate 3 to 5 days before eating.

title: play dough
directions: Mix ingredients and cook 3 minutes until mushy.
Pour on wax paper; knead a little.

title: hamburger sausage(summer sausage)
directions: Mix hamburger and spices well with your hands once a day for three days.
On day 4, form into rolls; place on cool cookie sheet.
Bake for 6 hours at 175°.

title: irish coffee
directions: In a bowl, beat cream, powdered sugar and vanilla until stiff. Refrigerate.
Prepare coffee using 3/4 cup ground and 3 cups water.
Drain.
Add 1 ounce
brandy and 2 teaspoons sugar to each mug; stir.
Pour hot coffee into each mug. Top with whipped cream and sprinkle with instant coffee.

title: broiled smelt
directions: Mix butter, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Clean smelt, splitting them open if they are large.
Dip each in butter mixture.
Roll in flour.
Place in double boiler rack.
Broil for 6 minutes.
Turn each once.
Serves 4.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well.
Form into balls.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: ginger ale punch
directions: Dilute orange juice and lemon juice according to directions on cans.
Mix fruit juice, sugar and water.
Add ginger ale just before serving, then 1 quart orange sherbet in center of punch bowl.
